<F P=100> Kyrgyzstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Akayev Receives Japanese Trade Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Akayev Receives Japanese Trade Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905143194 Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network in 
Kyrgyz 2300 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905143194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bishkek Kyrgyz Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kyrgyz </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Akayev received a Japanese delegation led 
by Naito Masahisa, director general of the international trade 
policy department of the Ministry of International Trade and 
Industry on 18 May at Government House. President Akayev 
thanked the government and people of Japan for the invaluable 
economic assistance rendered to Kyrgyzstan in this trying time. 
He said in particular that the Japanese are now looking into 
the complete reconstruction of Kyrgyzstan's banking system and 
the building of a complex of medical enterprises. He focused 
his attention in particular on the humanitarian aid Kyrgyzstan 
is now receiving. Akayev expressed his hope that Japanese 
business circles will actively invest in the Kyrgyz economy. 
The Kyrgyz side will generate all conditions to this effect. 
  In his turn, the head of the Japanese delegation thanked the 
host for a warm reception and said the specialists who are 
visiting the Republic will do their best to facilitate an uplift 
in the Kyrgyz economy. 
  On the same day, the Japanese delegation was received by 
Prime Minister Apas Dzhumagulov. The meeting was held in a 
businesslike and constructive atmosphere. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

