<F P=100> Uzbekistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   EU Program for Energy Saving, Power Engineering Outlined </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    EU Program for Energy Saving, Power Engineering Outlined </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905170294 Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN in Russian 0945 GMT 19 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tashkent UZBEKISTAN APN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today the presentation of the European Union's 
program on the development of power engineering and energy 
saving was held in Tashkent. This program consists of four 
large projects which covers all the areas in industry. The 
implementation of these projects will make it possible to save 
about 250 million kilowatt hours of energy annually. The 
European Union has allocated $7 million for this project. The 
program is already operating and in the first quarter of this 
year 218,000 tonnes of fuel units have been saved. 

</TEXT>

