<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Oppositionist Says Armenia Merged With Russia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Oppositionist Says Armenia Merged With Russia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1905130994 Moscow TRUD in Russian 19 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1905130994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow TRUD </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Own information" report: "Has Armenia Been Incorporated </F>
Into Russia?"] 
  [Text] The opposition newspaper AZATAMART has published a 
sensational statement by Edvard Oganesyan, a Dashnak Party 
leader, director of the Foundation for Russian-Armenian 
Relations, and former chief editor of Radio Liberty's Armenian 
programs, which claims, in particular, literally the following: 
"Incidentally, we have learned from Russian official circles 
that the Armenian Government has already signed an agreement on 
the Republic's incorporation into Russia. This fact is being 
persistently concealed from the people, although I do not think 
that the people will condemn their president because of this. 
This information is still unofficial, but if the facts about 
the signing of the agreement are confirmed, the government's 
initiative can be understood only if the agreement was signed 
with Russia's real masters." 
  How did the Armenian authorities react to this report? Levon 
Zurabyan the president's press secretary described this 
information as "gibberish and a completely groundless 
fabrication." 

</TEXT>

