<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Operations on Nakhichevan Border 18 May Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Operations on Nakhichevan Border 18 May Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905112094 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0744 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("LRAGIR," "HAYASTANI HANRAPETUTYUN", 
"YERKIR" dailies), 05/19/94 -- The situation at the 
Armenian-Azeri borders has aggravated again. "PAST" news agency 
reports, the Azeri army opened mortar fire in the direction of 
the village of Yeraskhavan in the Araratskiy district. Firing 
started at 2030 from the territory of Nakhichevan, and lasted 
till 0100. The Armenian frontier forces returned the fire. 
According to a "PAST" correspondent in Araratskiy district, 
military operations at the Nakhichevan borders have been 
continuing in the afternoon. "HAYASTANI HANRAPETUTYUN" reports, 
Nakhichevan units opened fire again at 0730 am on 18 May. 
Several casualties are reported in Yeraskhavan. The Armenian 
frontier forces refrained from returning the fire this time. 
  According to "YERKIR," quoting RA [Republic of Armenia] 
Defense Ministry press service, significant concentration of the 
Azeri army is reported at the Kapanskiy borders. 
  The Azeri units opened machine-gun fire in the direction of 
the village of Koti in the Noyemberyanskiy district. No 
casualties or significant property damage are reported. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

