<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijani Shelling of Karabakh Positions Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijani Shelling of Karabakh Positions Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905110694 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0744 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert ("LRAGIR", "AZG" dailies), 05/19/94 -- 
The Azeri troops continue shelling the Armenian defense 
positions in Mountainous Karabakh. 
  The enemy shelled the Armenian posts in the Mardakertskiy 
and 
Agdamskiy-Martuninskiy directions during the night and in the 
morning of 18 May, using artillery and tanks. One Karabakh 
soldier was reportedly injured. Military operations continued 
later during the day. Two Karabakh fighters were wounded at the 
village of Gulistan in the Shaumyaninskiy district as a result 
of Azeri shellings during the night of 17 May. The RMK [Republic 
of Mountainous Karabakh] defense forces refrained from returning 
the fire. 
  The enemy shelled the Karabakh defense positions at the 
villages of Seisulan and Karmiravan in the Mardakertskiy 
district, as well as the village of Yusifdzhanli in the 
Agdamskiy district, using large caliber machine guns and hand 
held weaponry. One soldier was wounded. 
  The Karabakh positions at the village of Gulistan were 
shelled again later in the afternoon. No casualties are reported. 
  At the same time, the Karabakh positions at the villages of 
Ashagi Abdurakmanli and Kurgan in the Fizulinskiy district have 
been shelled. The Karabakh side refrained from returning the 
fire in all mentioned cases. 

</TEXT>

