<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Front Lines `Tense,' Relatively Peaceful </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Front Lines `Tense,' Relatively Peaceful </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905191894 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in Azeri 1330 GMT 19 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905191894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] Defense Army 
Headquarters has disclosed that the situation at the front line 
is tense. However, no military operations were carried out 
today. The Armenian side has refrained from retaliating against 
the gunfire from the Azerbaijani military units at the defense 
positions from time to time. The situation on NKR's front line 
is relatively peaceful. 
  The areas along the border between Armenia and Azerbaijan 
have been fired on from Azerbaijan and the Nakhichevan 
Autonomous Republic from time to time during the past two days. 
The firing has caused damage and [words indistinct]. 
  According to the Armenian Ministry of Defense Press Service, 
the situation on the border was relatively peaceful today. The 
sides heeded the cease-fire agreement in the region. 
  We hope that peace and security will be gradually 
established 
on our common border. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

