<H3> <TI>   Press Secretary Hopes Azerbaijan To Show `Common Sense' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Secretary Hopes Azerbaijan To Show `Common Sense' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905064294 Yerevan SNARK in English 1454 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1905064294 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan, 18 May (SNARK)--Levon Zurabyan, acting 
press-secretary of the Armenian president, declared today that 
the sides of the Karabakh conflict have never been so close to 
peace as they are now. 
  "The road to the armistice is difficult, but the 
negotiations 
are going on and Armenia hopes that the Azerbaijani leadership 
will display common sense and sign the agreement," said Mr. 
Zurabyan at a briefing in Yerevan. He also declared that 
Armenia welcomes and highly estimates the readiness of Russia 
"to undertake the burden of peace-keeping forces' deployment in 
the region." 

</TEXT>

