<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Russia International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev: Russia Drafting Amendment to NATO's PFP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev: Russia Drafting Amendment to NATO's PFP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505150094 Moscow RIA in English 1244 GMT 15 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1505150094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Geneva, May 15, RIA -- We have come to the 
conclusion that the word "partnership" in the phrase partnership 
for peace should be given a deeper meaning, said Russia's 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. It will not be difficult to 
sign the existing Partnership for Peace document, and Russia has 
nothing against the framework agreement. 
  But since Russia believes that this document should be 
amended to take into account Russia's specific features and its 
relations with NATO, it will need time to draft the said 
document. It will not take long and the document is expected to 
be signed and formalised as a protocol, as President Yeltsin 
said in Bonn. Anyway, our intentions are serious and we are 
working hard to draft the document as soon as possible, Kozyrev 
said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
