<H3> <TI>   Grachev Urges Collective Security System in Pacific </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Grachev Urges Collective Security System in Pacific </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605151694 Moscow RIA in English 1350 GMT 6 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0605151694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 6 RIA -- Russian Defence Minister Pavel 
Grachev has said the Asia and Pacific region needs its own 
security system. Speaking at a press conference Friday he said 
the region where strategic interests of Russia, Japan, China, 
and the United States are closely intertwined lacks a mechanism 
to dovetail them. 
  He said Russia saw as its long-term strategic goal the 
formation of a collective security system involving all states 
situated in the region, and voiced confidence this initiative 
would be backed up by all states interested in maintaining peace 
and stability in the region. 

</TEXT>

