<H3> <TI>   Interpol To Help Russian Law Enforcement Agencies </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interpol To Help Russian Law Enforcement Agencies </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605210894 Moscow RIA in English 1651 GMT 6 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0605210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, May 6, RIA -- Foreign police officers 
will assist their Russian colleagues in combating the 
illegitimate transfer of capital from Russia to European 
countries. 
  According to Yuriy Melnikov, chief of the Interpol National 
Central Bureau in Russia, an understanding on this score was 
reached in the course of the 23rd European Interpol Regional 
Conference. 
  In the words of Melnikov, due to certain telecommunications 
measures, the system of prompt contacts between police services 
of 44 countries incorporated in European Interpol will be 
enhanced. The direct dialogue with colleagues from other 
countries, noted Melnikov, helped us clear up some particularly 
acute problems facing Russian law-enforcement officers, such as, 
the wide-scale penetration into the country of weapons of 
foreign make, including laser guns being bought by Russian 
Mafiosi. 

</TEXT>

