<H3> <TI>   Bomb Scare `False' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Bomb Scare `False' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305163194 Warsaw PAP in English 1614 GMT 13 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1305163194 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 13 -- Staff of the Polish Embassy in 
Moscow was evacuated Friday afternoon and the building was 
checked out for a bomb allegedly planted there after the embassy 
received a bomb threat by telephone. 
  A high-ranking Polish diplomat said that false bomb alarms 
are quite frequent in embassies in Moscow and they each time 
involve troublesome actions to make sure that people and 
buildings are safe. 

</TEXT>

