<H3> <TI>   Khabarovsk Leader Urges Abrogation of PRC Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khabarovsk Leader Urges Abrogation of PRC Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605112794 Moscow RIA in English 0903 GMT 6 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0605112794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khabarovsk, May 6, RIA -- Speaking at a press 
conference in Khabarovsk, Viktor Ishayev, head of the Khabarovsk 
territory's government, said that the government agreement 
between Russia and China, signed by Mikhail Gorbachev and his 
foreign minister Aleksandr Bessmertnykh in 1991, must be 
abrogated. Mr. Ishayev said that the agreement harmed the far 
eastern regions of Russia and the country as a whole and accused 
its authors of having failed to take into account many economic 
and historical factors. 
  Taking advantage of that agreement, the Chinese authorities 
want their civilian and military ships to be given free passage 
in the Russian waters along the Rivers Ussuri and Amur and 
demand that Russia cede to China a number of islands in the Amur. 
  "We want to trade and improve relations with China, but in 
doing so we shouldn't harm our own interests," Mr. Ishayev said. 

</TEXT>

