<H3> <TI>   Rybkin Urges Parliamentary Contacts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rybkin Urges Parliamentary Contacts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1505162194 Moscow RIA in English 1420 GMT 15 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1505162194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, May 15, RIA -- Satisfied with the talks 
with Chinese colleagues, Ivan Rybkin, chairman of the State Duma 
of the Federal Assembly of Russia, pointed to the importance of 
restoring Russo-Chinese parliamentary contacts at a briefing at 
the end of his delegation's second day in China. 
  "The talks are conducted in a businesslike and serious 
atmosphere," he said. The Russian delegation "is accumulating 
information vital for cooperation." The sides expressed 
interest in developing contacts between the north-eastern part 
of China and Siberia, exchanged opinion on international 
problems and discussed the situation in the planet's hot spots. 
  Rybkin said that good relations developed between the State 
Duma and the Russian Government in the past four months. He 
also said about potential candidates to the post of the Russian 
president: "We will continue to be short of leaders until we 
establish elections of administration heads." When asked if he 
would run for the post, Rybkin replied that many people don't 
suspect the burden of responsibilities of the president. 

</TEXT>

