<F P=103> LD1905094094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 19, RIA -- A State Duma delegation has 
returned from China in the early hours of May 19. It was 
staying there since May 14 at the invitation of the Chinese 
parliament's standing committee. The Russians met with state 
and communist leaders, visiting several enterprises and free 
economic zones. 
  According to Speaker Ivan Rybkin, the reforms must be 
implemented in a capable manner, with due respect toward history 
and traditions. He also stressed the need for economic and labor 
incentives. For his part, Mikhail Lapshin, leader of the 
Agrarian Party, says Russia shouldn't have destroyed the old 
system and that it ought to have borrowed some useful aspects as 
China had done. Vladimir Lukin, chairman of the Duma's 
foreign-affairs committee, stressed that the trip had corrected 
a small infatuation with Western-style politics and economics, 
saying that the Chinese economic-reform experience was quite 
interesting. 

</TEXT>

