<H3> <TI>   Chemical Weapons Facilities Being Dismantled </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chemical Weapons Facilities Being Dismantled </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805104094 Moscow RIA in English 0902 GMT 18 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1805104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cheboksary, May 18, RIA -- Russia starts to 
dismantle production facilities capable of manufacturing 
chemical weapons, said Vice-Premier Oleg Soskovets after 
visiting the Khimprom amalgamation in Chuvashia formerly 
cranking out chemical munitions. 
  The factory stopped producing chemical weapons in 1987, but 
the production facilities stood in place and could be 
re-activated when needed. 
  Oleg Soskovets and Chuvashian President Nikolay Fedorov 
decided to compile a schedule, before September 1, 1994, of 
phasing out chemical-capable production facilities. 

</TEXT>

