<H3> <TI>   Army To Adopt New Submachine Gun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army To Adopt New Submachine Gun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905155194 Moscow RIA in English 0916 GMT 19 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD1905155194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, May 19, RIA -- Russian troops will start 
receiving a new submachine gun already this year, said Chairman 
of the State Committee for Defence Industries Viktor Glukhikh. 
  The new gun developed by designer Ivanov is called Abakan 
and 
is said to surpass the Ak-74 currently used in the Russian Army. 
Glukhikh noted that Abakan has already been field tested and 
turned out to be a high-precision weapon. Its calibre is 
traditional for the Russian Army (7.62) and magazine contains 30 
cartridges. 
  Glukhikh said it was too early to say when the Army would 
adopt new submachine guns and speak about their exports. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

