<H3> <TI>   Peacekeepers Fired Upon in Ossetia-Ingushetia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peacekeepers Fired Upon in Ossetia-Ingushetia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005105194 Moscow RIA in English 0935 GMT 20 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2005105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladikavkaz, May 20, RIA -- Russian peacekeeping 
troops came under fire on two occasions in the state of 
emergency zone in North Ossetia and Ingushetia last night. 
  In the area of the village Nizhny Batakayurt in North 
Ossetia 
an armoured personnel carrier was shot at from the Niva car 
driving by. 
  In another incident a post of Russian Interior Ministry 
troops in Ingushetia came under fire from the direction of the 
village Dolakovo at 2 a.m.. 
  According to the press centre of the provisional 
administration of the zone under state of emergency, in both 
incidents Russian troops returned fire. No deaths or injuries 
resulting from the shooting were reported. 

</TEXT>

