<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Ukraine </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zlenko Rejects EU Agreement Link to NPT Membership </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zlenko Rejects EU Agreement Link to NPT Membership </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BR0905103694 London REUTER Textline Database in English 7 
May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> BR0905103694 </F>
<F P=104>  London REUTER Textline Database </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed article from Brussels EUROPE: "Ukraine: Kiev </F>
Affirms That Some Countries Hope To Link Signing of EU/Ukraine 
Agreement To NPT Membership"] 
  [Text] On the occasion of Sir Leon Brittan's visit, the 
Ukrainian Foreign Minister Anatoly Zlenko reproached a number of 
EU Member States with wanting to postpone signing of the 
agreement between Ukraine and the EU until Kiev belongs to the 
Non Proliferation Treaty [NPT]. "For the moment we are unable 
to say exactly which countries are involved, but we reject such 
an approach. We cannot accept such a link because Ukraine has 
done everything to speed up joining NPT", he told a press 
conference. Sir Leon Brittan said he was satisfied Ukraine was 
proceeding with nuclear disarmament despite the Kiev 
parliament's failure to join NPT. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

