<H3> <TI>   Law Guaranteeing Security of Foreign Investors Passed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Law Guaranteeing Security of Foreign Investors Passed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD0605112494 Moscow RIA in English 0903 GMT 6 May 94--FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD0605112494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow RIA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tashkent, May 6, RIA -- The Parliament of 
Uzbekistan, a former Soviet republic in Central Asia, has passed 
a law guaranteeing the security of foreign investments and 
foreign property and granting foreign investors a number of 
benefits. One of the clauses of the new legislation says that 
should any subsequent law deteriorate investment conditions, the 
legislation that was in force when the contract was signed would 
be applied to foreigners for 10 years. 
  Uzbekistan also plans to set up a state insurance company to 
protect its clients from political risks. The company's assets 
will be deposited in foreign banks. 

</TEXT>

