<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unemployment Up; Low-Skilled Labor Jobs Available </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Unemployment Up; Low-Skilled Labor Jobs Available </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC0705115894 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0836 GMT 7 May 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> NC0705115894 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Yerevan ("AZG" daily), 05/07/94 -- The number of 
employed population in Armenia decreased by 2 percent during the 
year and reached 511,000 by April 1. According to statistics, 
116,000 people have registered in employment offices, seeking 
for a job. Though the current number of available job positions 
is about 1684, these are mainly for low skilled labor, and only 
233 people were employed. 
  107,400 people, 68,100 of which women, had the status of 
unemployed by April 1. The number of unemployed increased 1.4 
times compared with the previous year. 
  The number of those receiving unemployment grants decreased 
by 8,900 compared with the previous month. Only 22.3 percent of 
unemployed are currently receiving grants. Average unemployment 
grant was 95.4 drams by April 1. 
  Unemployment ratio in the republic was 6.6 percent in March 
of this year, having increased by 1.9 points compared with the 
previous year. 

</TEXT>

