<H3> <TI>   Interior Minister Yerin Ends Visit to Sakhalin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Minister Yerin Ends Visit to Sakhalin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005093094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0410 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005093094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Yevgeniy Belovitskiy] </F>
  [Text] Yuzhno-Sakhalinsk, 20 May -- Viktor Yerin, Russian 
Federation minister of interior, ended his visit to Sakhalin. 
At a news conference today on the results of the trip, the 
minister stressed he came to Sakhalin to acquaint himself with 
the work of the Interior Ministry bodies in the island oblast 
and to resolve the question of giving aid to the leadership of 
the oblast's directorate of internal affairs. The minister 
announced that in accordance with the results of a check that 
was carried out prior to his visit by an Interior Ministry 
commission, a number of responsible officials of the oblast 
directorate had been punished and measures were worked out to 
strengthen law and order on Sakhalin and in the Kurils. 
  In connection with the Putina-94 operation that is being 
carried out in the Russian Far East, Viktor Yerin described it 
as very expedient in the struggle against organized 
international crime. The minister believes concrete contacts 
between the island's Interior Ministry bodies and the police of 
Japan's most northerly island, Hokkaido, could be very 
beneficial. 

</TEXT>

