<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Petersburg Firm To Build German Turbines </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Petersburg Firm To Build German Turbines </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2005085994 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 18 May 94 p 
6 </F>

<F P=103> PM2005085994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "`Siemens' Technology Introduced in </F>
St. Petersburg"] 
  [Text] The Russian-German "Interturbo" enterprise has set 
up serial production of 150-megawatt gas turbines, assembled 
using Siemens technology. In electric power stations using, for 
example, the steam and gas energy production cycle, such 
turbines generate almost double the output produced by the 
industrial energy systems of thermal electric power stations. 
Interturbo, which was set up by Siemens and the St. Petersburg 
firm LMZ, was initially geared toward production of "high 
technology" goods enjoying a stable demand in power engineering 
worldwide. 
  In the first phase of the enterprise's work the St. 
Petersburgers are to assemble units from components delivered 
from Germany. At the same time the infrastructure for the 
production of components and machine parts in Russian plants is 
to be set up. Within a few years deliveries of these items will 
dominate the list of turbine components, so the 
production-sharing program envisages. The high quality of 
Interturbo's ouput is confirmed by the international certificate 
issued by experts of the German Technical Oversight Association. 

</TEXT>

