<F P=102>   MK2005074094 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 20 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK2005074094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations Press Service </F>
report under the "News" rubric: "Radioactive Waste Could End Up 
In Ocean"] 
  [Text] This could happen, specialists think, unless urgent 
measures are taken at the "Zvezda" plant in Maritime Kray to set 
up facilities for the dumping, storing, and recycling of liquid 
radioactive waste. 
  Looking for a way out from the current situation, the 
Russian 
government sent a number of instructions to interested 
ministries and departments. But as is always the case, the 
whole thing is held up for want of funds. Anatoliy Shumilov, 
deputy chief of the Russian Ministry of Emergency Situations' 
man-made and natural emergency situations administration, a 
regular meeting will be held in June of representatives of 
interested ministries and departments which will perhaps make 
the optimal decision. 

</TEXT>

