<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Communique Describes Cease-Fire Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Communique Describes Cease-Fire Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1905192794 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1905192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Text" of a Azerbaijan Ministry of Defense Press Service </F>
communique dated 18 May -- read by announcer] 
  [Text] The mass media have made conflicting reports over 
the past few days on the outcome of the talks held by the 
defense ministers of Russia, Azerbaijan, and Armenia in Moscow. 
The Azerbaijan Ministry of Defense Press Service deems it 
essential to outline the following: 
  An agreement on a cease-fire was reached at the talks. It 
was also agreed that there should be an opportunity for the 
negotiating parties to work on the final document in a peaceful 
atmosphere. The document was not signed because several of its 
paragraphs were not consistent with each other. An experts 
group is working on it. The defense ministers of Russia, 
Azerbaijan, and Armenia will hold a new round of talks when the 
experts conclude their work. 
  Meanwhile, the situation in the operations zone has been 
relatively peaceful during the past few days. However, our 
military positions in various parts of the front line have been 
fired upon. Sadarak in the Nakhichevan Autonomous Republic was 
also fired on with PDM's [not further specified] and mortars 
last night. Azerbaijan's military forces ignored these 
provocative activities and refrained from returning fire. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

