<H3> <TI>   Karabakh Signs First Interstate Treaty With Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Karabakh Signs First Interstate Treaty With Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005074594 Yerevan SNARK in English 1108 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2005074594 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan SNARK </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Simferopol, 19 May (SNARK) -- Nagorno-Karabakh 
Republic [NKR] has signed its first interstate treaty. As SNARK 
newsman reported from Simferopol, the comprehensive treaty 
between Nagorno-Karabakh and Crimean Republic was signed by the 
NKR Defense Committee Chairman Robert Kocharyan and by Crimean 
Republic President Yuri Meshkov. Parties observed that the 
signed document will serve a good basis for cooperation in 
political, economic, cultural, and other spheres. 
  The treaty has been signed during the visit of Karabakh 
delegation in Crimea who attended the meetings related with 50th 
anniversary of Crimean Tatar deportation. 
  As note the observers, the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic -- yet 
unrecognized in the world -- has no such treaty signed with any 
country, not even Armenia. 
  Today the Karabakh delegation left Simferopol for home. 

</TEXT>

