<H3> <TI>   Relative Lull Continues in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Relative Lull Continues in Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905122694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1124 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905122694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A lull continues in the zone of the Armenian-Azeri 
conflict, Interfax was told on Thursday [19 May] by a spokesman 
for the Defense Army staff of Nagorno-Karabakh. 
  The two sides are observing the cease-fire from 0000 hours 
of 
17 May. 
  A source in the Azeri Defense Ministry also reported to 
INTERFAX on the relative calm in the zone of the conflict. 
  The source said the Armenians had fired on 18 May and on the 
morning of the 19th at the positions of the Azeri Army in the 
Terter and Geranboy directions. Some border villages of 
Azerbaijan were shelled from the territory of Armenia. 
  The source claimed that the Azeri Army, in compliance with 
the conditions of the truce, did not retaliate. 

</TEXT>

