<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "NEGA Reports" rubric: </F>
"Azerbaijan"] 
  [Text] The council of Democratic Congress chairmen held a 
regular meeting at the head office of the Azerbaijani Democratic 
Party. Participants in the meeting discussed the sociopolitical 
situation in the Republic. The meeting adopted a plan for the 
peaceful settlement of the Armenian-Azerbaijani conflict drawn 
up by Democratic Congress members, which is seen as an 
alternative to the Russian peace plan. In the near future the 
plan will be passed to the Azerbaijani National Assembly for 
consideration. In addition, the member parties of the 
Democratic Congress issued a joint statement on the signing of 
the Bishkek protocol by Azerbaijani parliament speaker Rasul 
Guliyev on 8 May. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

