<F P=103> NC2005033294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku TURAN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baku, 19 May (TURAN)--The session of Azerbaijan's 
Democratic Congress completed last evening. The agenda included 
only one question -- return of Russian troops to Azerbaijan. 
  The participants of the session unanimously adopted the 
resolution which condemns the activities of the current 
leadership of the republic aimed at "return of Russian troops to 
the country". The resolution reads that "if Russian troops be 
brought to Azerbaijan, the Democratic Congress reserves right to 
conduct rallies of protest." 
  The Democratic Congress was founded on 23 March 1994. It 
includes five opposition parties: Musavat, the Popular Front, 
the Democratic Party, the Party of Nation's Liberty, and Ana 
Torpag Party. 

