<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Urges Amendment to Signed Protocol on Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Urges Amendment to Signed Protocol on Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005113294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1055 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005113294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 20 May TASS -- Azerbaijan's Defence Minister 
Mamadrafi Mammadov, who arrived in Moscow on Thursday, has not 
yet signed the protocol on ceasefire and disengagement of the 
warring troops, which was prepared for signing on 17 May. 
  Azerbaijan's Ambassador to Russia Ramiz Rizayev told 
ITAR-TASS that the Moscow meetings between the Azeri minister 
and Russia's Deputy Defence Minister Georgiy Kondratyev have 
failed to identify "common approaches, and Mamadrafi Mammadov 
intends to meet Russian Defence Minister Pavel Grachev today. 
  Azerbaijan insists on the withdrawal of the Armenian troops 
from the territories captured simultaneously with the ceasefire 
and disengagement of troops. It calls for recording this 
provision in the protocol. "We would like to combine the first 
and the second phases of the settlement of the conflict," 
Azerbaijan's ambassador told ITAR-TASS. 
  According to Ramiz Rizayev, Azerbaijan's proposals have met 
with support in principle of the Russian minister of foreign 
affairs, Andrey Kozyrev. 
  Experts of the Russian Defence Ministry do not think that 
Pavel Grachev will agree to the amendments to the protocol 
proposed by Azerbaijan. The protocol as is has already been 
signed by representatives of Armenia, Nagorno-Karabakh and 
Russia. 

</TEXT>

