<H3> <TI>   Abkhaz Council of Ministers Meets in Extended Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhaz Council of Ministers Meets in Extended Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1805132294 Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network in Georgian 0800 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1805132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi Radio Tbilisi Network </F>
<F P=105>  Georgian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] According to the press center of the Abkhazian 
Council of Ministers an extended session of the Council of 
Ministers has been held. An in-depth report on the Moscow 
agreement of 14 May 1994, on a ceasefire and the separation of 
forces was made by Zurab Erkvania, a member of the Georgian 
delegation at the talks and chairman of the Council of Ministers 
of the Autonomous Republic of Abkhazia. 
  Proceeding from the current realistic situation, the session 
supported the agreement and drew up the relevant measures. 
  The session discussed and adopted a resolution on the work 
of 
the Abkhaz Council of Ministers and immediate measures for 
stepping up its activity. 
  The leadership of the Council of Ministers of the Autonomous 
Republic of Abkhazia met with a large group of refugees from 
Gali rayon. In a sincere and principled conversation, the two 
sides discussed the Moscow agreement on the settlement of the 
Georgian-Abkhaz conflict. Suggestions on creating mechanisms 
for carrying out safely and economically the first stage of the 
return of refugees were worked out. 

</TEXT>

