<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Culture, Science Workers Join Social Accord Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Culture, Science Workers Join Social Accord Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905153194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1220 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905153194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Olga Svistunova and Igor Veksler] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 19 TASS -- "The signing of an agreement 
on civic accord which began 20 days ago gave a positive impetus 
to socio-political processes in the Russian Federation. The 
document changes the character of political relations in the 
country and creates a basis for the beginning of the unification 
of all strata of Russian society," said Chairman of the 
Federation Council Vladimir Shumeyko, opening a signing ceremony 
which took place in the St. Vladimir Hall in the Grand Kremlin 
Palace today. 
  Representatives of creative associations, scientific 
organisations, workers of culture and science put their 
signatures under the agreement. 
  The process of signing the agreement began by a ceremonial 
act in the Kremlin attended by the Russian president, prime 
minister, representatives of both chambers of the Russian 
parliament, representatives of the subjects of the Federation, 
leaders of a number of parties, public and religious 
associations. The agreement is open to representatives of any 
political forces coming out for peace and accord in the country, 
for strengthening state power and surmounting the socio-economic 
crisis. 

</TEXT>

