<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Rejects Resignation of Moscow Intelligence Chief </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Rejects Resignation of Moscow Intelligence Chief </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1905115094 Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS in Russian 19 May 
94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> MK1905115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under the "Hold the Front Page!" </F>
rubric: "Moscow Chekists Came Close to Losing Their Head"] 
  [Text] MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS has learned from reliable 
sources that yesterday the president turned down a resignation 
request from Major General Yevgeniy Savostyanov, chief of 
Moscow's directorate of the Russian Federation Federal 
Counterintelligence Service [FCS]. 
  Rumors of Savostyanov's imminent resignation had been around 
for several weeks. The request was finally written but turned 
down. Various things are being said about the major general's 
wish to resign. According to one guess, Savostyanov decided to 
go into politics. Many staffers in his directorate however 
think their boss is simply in a hurry. MOSKOVSKIY KOMSOMOLETS 
has information that Sergey Stepashin, FCS director, would like 
to see Cherkasov, the current chief of the St. Petersburg FCS 
directorate, occupying the Moscow directorate. Stepashin has 
been friends with Cherkasov for a long time and he interceded 
for him at the time of the repeat certification procedure. 

</TEXT>

