<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Aide Calls For More Rapid Reforms </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Aide Calls For More Rapid Reforms </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1805154194 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 18 May 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1805154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report under "In the Government" rubric: </F>
"Danger of Pressure From Lobby Groups"] 
  [Text] For the few months it has been in power Viktor 
Chernomyrdin's government has managed to achieve a positive 
result as regards curbing inflation, but there is a danger that 
the cabinet, under pressure from agrarian and 
military-industrial complex lobby groups, will make undesirable 
adjustments to monetary and credit policy. This was stated by 
Yevgeniy Yasin, leader of the Russian Federation president's 
analysis center. 
  In his opinion the rate of the reforms has slowed down 
somewhat in the same period. "We could and should have moved 
faster," he said. Yasin believes that the government's main 
task is "not to hold up the processes begun in 1992 but to 
provide the opportunity to implement the transformations at the 
level of enterprises and regions." 

</TEXT>

