<H3> <TI>   RIA-NOVOSTI Charter Ratified 3 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    RIA-NOVOSTI Charter Ratified 3 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1905120394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 May 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1905120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Decree no. 429 of the Russian Federation Government "On </F>
Ratifying the Charter of the RUSSIAN INFORMATION 
AGENCY-NOVOSTI," signed by V. Chernomyrdin, chairman of the 
Russian Federation Government, and dated 3 May 1994] 
  [Text] In accordance with Russian Federation [RF] 
presidential edict no. 2278 of 23 December 1993 "On Ensuring the 
Activity of the RUSSIAN INFORMATION AGENCY-NOVOSTI" the RF 
Government decrees that: 
  1. The appended RUSSIAN INFORMATION AGENCY-NOVOSTI Charter 
adopted by the labor collective of the RUSSIAN INFORMATION 
AGENCY-NOVOSTI (hereinafter RIA-NOVOSTI) is to be ratified. 
  2. The RF State Committee for the Management of State 
Property is to officially register in accordance with prescribed 
procedure the assignation to RIA-NOVOSTI of property which is in 
federal ownership, along with property acquired with federal 
budget funds and used by the agency to pursue its statutory 
activity. 
  3. As of 1994 the RF Ministry of the Economy, when deciding 
the basic indicators of the RF state investment program, is to 
stipulate for RIA-NOVOSTI in a separate paragraph the limits of 
state centralized capital investments funded from the federal 
budget for capital construction and the acquisition of equipment. 
  4. The Moscow Government is to be advised to consider the 
question of allocating to RIA-NOVOSTI a downtown plot of land 
for the construction of an apartment block for agency personnel. 
  5. The Moscow Oblast Administration is to be advised to 
consider the question of allocating a three-hectare plot of land 
in the vicinity of Moscow for individual construction and 
development by RIA-NOVOSTI staffers. 
  6. RIA-NOVOSTI is to be authorized to build an editorial and 
production complex. 
  7. Point 1, Paragrah 1 of RF Council of Ministers-Government 
decree no. 922 of 16 September 1993 "Questions of the RUSSIAN 
INFORMATION AGENCY-NOVOSTI" (SOBRANIYE AKTOV PREZIDENTA I 
PRAVITELSTVA ROSSIYSKOY FEDERATSII No. 38, 1993, p 3577) is to 
be deemed invalid. 
  [Signed] V. Chernomyrdin, chairman of the RF Government 
  [Dated] Moscow, 3 May 1994 
  Editorial Office note: The RIA-NOVOSTI Charter is not cited. 

</TEXT>

