<DATE1>  19 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Military Rapid Deployment Force Formed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Military Rapid Deployment Force Formed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905192894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1815 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 19 TASS -- Russia sets up a new structure 
in its armed Forces -- mobile forces which will include rapid 
deployment forces and instant reaction forces, Colonel-General 
Vladimir Semyonov, commander-in-chief of these forces, told a 
news conference at the main headquarters of the land forces 
today. 
  According to the general, these changes are envisaged by the 
military reform and requirements of the main provisions of 
Russia's military doctrine. Vladimir Semyonov called the 
establishment of the mobile forces a "coerced measure". 
  "We were forced to do this due to the current political 
situation in Russia and the new views developed by military 
science and strategy," the commander-in-chief said. 
  The mobile forces, the colonel-general noted, will be used 
at 
a "threatening period". With the outbreak of local and other 
conflicts, Vladimir Semyonov noted, these forces will be moved 
to the necessary regions "for a short period of time". For 
instant- reaction forces this period will be twenty-four hours 
and for rapid deployment forces -- several days. 
  The commander-in-chief determined some tasks to be resolved 
by the mobile forces: The inadmissibility of spreading of local 
conflicts, the localization of large scale conflicts and the 
creation of conditions for strategical deployment of Russian 
Armed Forces. 
  The colonel-general believes that the mobile forces will be 
best staffed in the Russian Armed Forces. They will also 
include units and subunits of land and airborne troops, military 
transport and combat aircraft and other units from fighting 
services and branches of arms. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

