<H3> <TI>   New Multipurpose Aircraft Makes Maiden Flight </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Multipurpose Aircraft Makes Maiden Flight </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1905105594 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 19 May 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1905105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report from ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, ITAR-TASS </F>
column under the "Yesterday, Today, Tomorrow" rubric: "Ilyushin 
On Order"] 
  [Text] A new-type Il-103 developed by the S. Ilyushin 
Experimental Design Bureau has made its maiden flight at an 
airfield in Zhukovskoye, near Moscow. 
  This small, multirole aircraft fitted with an engine 
manufactured by the U.S. firm Teledyne Continental Motors is 
destined to carry passengers or freight, for pilot instruction 
and training, environmental monitoring, or the delivery of 
emergency medical aid. Series production will be carried out at 
the Lukhovitsy Aircraft Plant. There are already plenty of 
orders for the aircraft, including some from foreign companies. 

</TEXT>

