<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Command Urges Peaceful Settlement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Command Urges Peaceful Settlement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005125494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1229 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Shevtsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- The Black Sea navy command 
today called on all the political leaders, involved in the 
current events in the Crimea, to do their best to settle all the 
arising disputes by peaceful political means. 
  Political instability in the Crimea and the situation around 
naval bases, says an official statement issued by the Black Sea 
navy press centre today, engenders moral and psychological 
tension in military units. No matter how the situation 
develops, the Black Sea navy will not be able to keep aloof of 
the processes occurring around it. This alarms the command of 
the navy, its officers and noncoms. 
  The statement says that not a single regional conflict was 
solved by armed force over the past twenty years. The wars in 
Nagorno- Karabakh, Yugoslavia and Abkhazia show that the 
ordinary people suffer from the hostilities, but not those who 
unleash them. The Black Sea navy command relies on the wisdom 
and good will of the peoples and the political representative 
they had elected. 
  The winter training is about to end on the Black Sea navy. 
The press centre's statement says that exercises of different 
forces are proceeding according to schedule. Taking part in 
them are warships, auxiliary vessels, and aircraft. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

