<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev, CE Official Discuss Human Rights </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev, CE Official Discuss Human Rights </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905155694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1357 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Yuriy Kozlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 19 TASS -- Struggle against nationalism 
in all its manifestations, for strict observance of human rights 
should become a top priority area of cooperation between Russia 
and the Council of Europe, said here on Thursday Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev at a meeting with Miguel Angel Marinez, 
president of the parliamentary assembly of the Council of Europe. 
  The minister noted that the Russian side feels concern over 
the position of the Russian-speaking people in the Baltics. 
  Kozyrev confirmed Russia's desire to join the Council of 
Europe and expressed hope that the practical solution of this 
issue will not take more than one year. 
  The minister noted that May 21 marks another anniversary of 
Andrey Sakharov's birth, a date which traditionally fills the 
hearts of honest Russian people with a hope for the successful 
continuation of the cause of this outstanding champion for human 
rights. 
  "I believe that Russia will be Sakharov's Russia rather than 
Zhirinovskiy's," stressed Kozyrev. He underlined that the 
operating Constitution and democratically elected Russian 
parliament are a guarantee that the present changes will be 
irreversible. 

</TEXT>

