<H4>    Moscow-Paris Hotline To Be Set Up </H4>

<F P=102> LD1905191594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1744 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, 19 May -- A hotline is to be set up between 
the residences of the presidents of Russia and France -- between 
the Kremlin and the Elysee palace. An agreement on this was 
concluded today in Moscow by Russia's Minister of Foreign 
Affairs Andrey Kozyrev and his French counterpart Alain Juppe. 
The solemn ceremony of signing the document took place after 
the conversation between the heads of the foreign policy 
departments which lasted for two and a half hours at the mansion 
of the Russian Ministry of Foreign Affairs had ended. 

</TEXT>

