<H3> <TI>   Reportage on French Foreign Minister Juppe's Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on French Foreign Minister Juppe's Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Churkin Reviews Chernomyrdin-Juppe Talks </H4>

<F P=102> LD2005104594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0941 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005104594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 May -- An agreement on partnership and 
cooperation between Russia and the European Community [EC] will 
be ready for initialling in June this year. This was stated 
today by Russian Federation Deputy Foreign Minister Vitaliy 
Churkin upon completion of Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin's 
talks with French Foreign Minister Alain Juppe. 
  Vitaliy Churkin said Alain Juppe assured Viktor Chernomyrdin 
of France's readiness in the near future to join Russia in 
resolving the question of the trade in products of the nuclear 
cycle. The special position adopted by France in this area has 
so far held back the talks on concluding a cooperation agreement 
between Russia and the EC. Russia and France are, of course, 
major producers of fuel for nuclear power stations and compete 
in European markets. 
  A number of questions relating to bilateral trade-economic 
cooperation were also discussed at the talks. Alain Juppe 
handed Viktor Chernomyrdin an invitation from French Prime 
Minister Eduard Balladur to visit France in the second half of 
this year. The invitation was accepted. 

</TEXT>

