<H3> <TI>   Military Chiefs Differ on Peace Role in Karabakh </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Chiefs Differ on Peace Role in Karabakh </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005101794 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0900 GMT 
20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Col-Gen [Vladimir] Semenov, commander in chief of 
ground forces, said the recent talks in Moscow on the Karabakh 
conflict must be regarded as abortive as the Azerbaijanis have 
failed to sign the final document. A similar assessment was 
already made by Col-Gen [Yevgeniy] Podkolzin, commander of 
airborne forces. He also believes airborne forces cannot be 
dispatched to the region without the consent of Baku 
authorities. However, according to the SNARK agency, Russian 
Defense Minister Pavel Grachev does favor the dispatch of 
Russian forces to the Karabakh region. 

</TEXT>

