<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Cites `Domestic Problems' as Reason </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Cites `Domestic Problems' as Reason </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005063494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0630 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005063494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Ivan Zakharchenko] </F>
  [Text] Seoul May 20 -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on 
Friday sent a personal message to President Kim Yong-sam of the 
Republic of Korea about a postponement of the first session of 
the Russian-South Korean Intergovernmental Commission for 
Economic Cooperation, according to diplomatic sources in Seoul. 
  The sources said the letter explains that the commission's 
session, which was previously scheduled to be held on Seoul on 
May 20, has been postponed because Aleksandr Shokhin, 
vice-premier and minister of economics, cannot arrive in South 
Korea "due to purely domestic problems". 
  Yeltsin suggested that the commission hold a session in 
Moscow before Kim's visit to Russia. The visit is scheduled for 
June 1-4. 

</TEXT>

