<H3> <TI>   Yarov To Replace Shokhin in Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yarov To Replace Shokhin in Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905195594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1616 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905195594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vice Premier and Economics Minister Aleksandr 
Shokhin cannot fly to Korea on Thursday as planned. Interfax 
learned at Shokhin's office that Yuriy Yarov would go in his 
place. 
  Officials said that the change had been made at the request 
of Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin who had given Shokhin 
urgent work, the nature of which is unknown. They denied 
reports that the incident was linked to a possible changes in 
the government. 
  Shokhin had intended to spend two days in Seoul and discuss 
bilateral trade and economic cooperation. 

</TEXT>

