<H3> <TI>   ROK Company To Build Russian Yak Aircraft </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ROK Company To Build Russian Yak Aircraft </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2005083594 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 18 May 94 p 
6 </F>

<F P=103> PM2005083594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Russian Planes From the Korean </F>
Conveyor Belt"] 
  [Text] Russian airplanes will soon be produced by plants 
in South Korea, thanks to a joint company set up by the South 
Korean "Khendz" [name as transliterated] corporation and the 
Russian A.S. Yakovlev Experimental Design Bureau. Production of 
"Yak" aircraft is expected to begin in the course of the year. 
  The "Khendz-Yak Aerospace" joint venture, in which the South 
Korean side will have a 51-percent share and the Russian 
experimental design bureau 49 percent, plans to produce 
medium-sized and small aircraft. It is expected that in the 
future the joint venture will be able to sell its output abroad, 
notably in the United States and European countries. 

</TEXT>

