<F P=103> LD1905124394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk has sent a 
message to Russian President Yeltsin where he expresses hope for 
the earliest solution of the Black Sea Fleet problem. As it has 
become known to INTERFAX, in his message the Kravchuk expresses 
regret over what he describes as the unconstructive stand taken 
by the Russian delegation at the talks on the Black Sea Fleet 
which took place in Sebastopol [Sevastopol] in April. 
  Kravchuk said about the need to divide the fleet in line 
with 
the Moscow understandings of 15 April (according to the 
understandings Russia possesses 80 pct of the Fleet and Ukraine 
-- 20 percent). 
  The Ukrainian President voiced the need to attach a special 
status to the Marines. 

