<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reiterates Supremacy of Kiev </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reiterates Supremacy of Kiev </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905192194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1651 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905192194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko, </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev, 19 May -- "We shall act decisively and 
consistently in the defense of the territorial integrity of 
Ukraine. We shall act within the bounds of the Constitution, of 
our powers, precisely proceeding from the fact that the Crimea 
is a component part of Ukraine, as registered in the 
constitutions of our state and the Republic of Crimea." This 
was stated by President Leonid Kravchuk at a press conference 
today. 
  He dwelt on the latest events in the Crimea when the Supreme 
Soviet of this autonomous republic intends to examine the issue 
of restoring a number of clauses of the Crimea's Constitution in 
the edition of 6 May 1992. In particular, this relates to the 
inclusion of the Crimea in the composition of Ukraine, to dual 
citizenship, the setting up of military formations and others. 
"If the Supreme Soviet of the Crimea adopts these documents, I 
shall immediately submit to the parliament of the Ukraine a 
draft decision on suspending their effect," the President said. 
  "Solving these issues is exclusively within the competence 
of 
the Supreme Soviet of Ukraine," Leonid Kravchuk stressed. 
Ignoring this fundamental situation registered in the law "On 
Demarcation of Powers Between the Bodies of State Power of 
Ukraine and the Republic of Crimea," is fraught with serious 
consequences for those who set foot on that path. 
  "For each society, for each state, there is a pale beyond 
which no one is allowed to step," the president pointed out. 
Those who ignore this, those who are guided by ambitions and by 
other principles, should remember that their actions are 
unlawful. They should know that such actions, will primarily 
have an effect on the entire population of the Crimea. Those 
who, ignoring the existing legislation and international legal 
norms, cause the situation to heat up, will have to answer for 
this. No one will evade the responsibility, regardless of what 
high regalia and powers he might be in cooperation with, the 
head of the Ukrainian state stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

