<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Plans Direct Presidential Rule in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Plans Direct Presidential Rule in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905181294 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1600 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905181294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The FRANCE PRESSE AGENCY has reported, quoting 
sources in the Ukrainian president's entourage, that Leonid 
Kravchuk is planning to introduce direct presidential rule in 
the Crimea. However, the final decision will depend on the 
consultations currently held between Russia, Ukraine, the United 
States, and Crimean authorities. The consultations began after 
more than 1,000 Ukrainian servicemen were sent to the peninsula 
last night. 
  The Ukrainian Interior Ministry today denied the report that 
the troops had been brought in but confirmed the fact that the 
Crimean Interior Ministry had been transformed into the Crimean 
Directorate for Internal Affairs of Ukraine, and that Colonel 
Vladimir Chernyshov had been appointed its head. 

</TEXT>

