<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Reorganizes Crimean Security Ministries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Reorganizes Crimean Security Ministries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905165794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1537 
GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail </F>
Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev, 19 May -- By today's decrees Ukrainian 
President Leonid Kravchuk has reorganized the power ministries 
[defense, interior, and internal affairs] of the Republic of 
Crimea, despite the fact that he does not have a constitutional 
right to do so. 
  Main directorates will be set up on the basis of the 
Ukrainian Security Service and the Interior Ministry. They will 
be subordinated directly to the Ukrainian Security Service 
chairman and the Ukrainian Interior Minister. Administrative 
and service premises, armaments, means of transport, and 
property which in the past were used by the Security Service and 
the Interior Ministry of the Republic of Crimea are being handed 
over to them. 
  Major General Ivan Kolomitsev has been appointed by Leonid 
Kravchuk as chief of the main directorate of the Ukrainian 
security service in Crimea. 
  ITAR-TASS has learned that by decision of the Cabinet of 
Ministers, an additional post of deputy minister and chief of 
the Main Directorate of Internal Affairs in the Crimea has been 
introduced onto the staff of the central apparatus of the 
Ukrainian Interior Ministry. Militia Colonel Valeriy Chernyshov 
has been appointed to this post. 
  By decree of the Ukrainian president, the Ministry of 
Justice 
of the Republic of Crimea has also been reorganized into the 
main directorate of justice in the Crimea. From now on it will 
be subordinate to the Ukrainian Ministry of Justice. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-63248 </DOCNO>
