<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Directive Subordinates Security Service </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Directive Subordinates Security Service </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005091894 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005091894 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] With the aim of increasing effectiveness in 
performing the missions that are entrusted to the Security 
Service of Ukraine, improving coordination in carrying out the 
operative and investigative operations to ensure security, and 
in accordance with Paragraphs 3 (?and) 7.1 of Article 114.5 in 
our state's constitution, Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk by 
his directive has reorganized the Security Service of the 
Republic of Crimea into the Security Service of Ukraine Main 
Directorate in Crimea, subordinate directly to the Security 
Service of Ukraine chairman, with the administrative and 
logistical facilities, weapons, transportation means and 
property, that are currently being used by the Security Service 
of the Republic of Crimea, transferred to his use. 
  The directive introduces the post of chief of the Security 
Service of Ukraine Main Directorate in Crimea and appoints 
Maj-Gen Ivan Kolomyytsev to that post. 
  The chairman of the Security Service of Ukraine is to 
approve 
within the term of 10 days the complement of the Security 
Service of Ukraine Main Directorate in Crimea. 
  The directive is effective as of the day of issue. 

</TEXT>

