<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Ignores Kravchuk's Decree </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meshkov Ignores Kravchuk's Decree </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2005083694 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2005083694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The new Crimean Supreme Council has taken yet 
another step toward deterioration of relations with official 
Kiev. At its session yesterday, the Crimean legislature 
approved, with a majority of votes, the nomination of General 
Lepikhov, who was nominated by [Crimean] President Yuriy 
Meshkov, as chief of the Crimean Security Service. In this way, 
it ignored the decree issued by Ukrainian President Kravchuk 
reorganizing the Crimean Republic Security Service and the 
Ukrainian Security Service [SBU] General Department in the 
Crimea. The SBU press service in Kiev emphasizes that the main 
goal of the reorganization is to increase centralization of the 
service leadership and the effectiveness of its fight against 
organized crime in the Crimea, where it is assuming more and 
more dangerous forms. 
  Through the NOVYNY television and radio agency, the press 
service also reports that Crimean President Meshkov has 
practically ignored a wire sent to him by SBU Chief Yevhen 
Marchuk. The wire informs him that the SBU General Department 
in the Crimea, established in accordance with Leonid Kravchuk's 
decree, shall remain unchanged, in terms of its function, staff, 
and number. 
  The press service also reports that SBU First Deputy Chief 
Valeriy Malikov is currently in Simferopol with a group of SBU 
workers. They are preparing materials concerning the fight 
against organized crime in the Crimea, which will be examined at 
the next meeting of the SBU Collegium. 

</TEXT>

