<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today's session of the Crimean parliament adopted a 
law restoring the Constitution of 6 May 1992, INTERFAX reports. 
This Constitution envisions that the legal basis of relations 
between Ukraine and Crimea will be a treaty. It also stipulates 
that inhabitants of the peninsula are entitled to dual 
citizenship. 
  As has already been reported, Ukraine's President Leonid 
Kravchuk earlier warned that if the Crimean Supreme Soviet 
restores the Constitution, he will immediately ask the Ukrainian 
parliament to suspend the decision. 

</TEXT>

