<H3> <TI>   Black Sea Fleet Threatens To Intervene in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Black Sea Fleet Threatens To Intervene in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005100694 Paris AFP in English 0952 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2005100694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sevastopol, Ukraine, May 20 (AFP) -- The Black Sea 
Fleet, shared between the Ukraine and Russia, threatened Friday 
[20 May] to intervene in Crimea after the region's parliament 
adopted a new constitution effectively declaring independence 
from Kiev. 
  "It is clear that whatever the development of the situation, 
the Black Sea Fleet cannot remain outside events unfolding 
around it," the Fleet's Press Office said in a statement. 

</TEXT>

