<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Approves of Moroz as Supreme Council Head </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Approves of Moroz as Supreme Council Head </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905203294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1902 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and Mikhail </F>
Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev May 19 TASS -- "When electing Aleksandr Moroz 
chairman of the supreme soviet of Ukraine, deputies were guided, 
in my view, not only by political considerations but also by 
their own opinion of the personality of the contender", 
President Leonid Kravchuk of Ukraine said in reply to a question 
by ITAR-TASS about his attitude towards Wednesday elections. 
  During four years of work in the previous composition of the 
supreme soviet, Aleksandr Moroz was taking an active position in 
the parliament, had his own point of view on political, economic 
and legal problems of current life and upheld them quietly and 
with good reasoning, the president noted. 
  "I do not remember a case when he offended someone in the 
heat of a debate or showed haste in making decisions. By having 
elected Aleksandr Moroz deputies hope that he will be able to 
unite all of them for constructive work," Leonid Kravchuk 
pointed out. 
  "For me this is also a determining factor. We may have 
unlike and even quite different viewpoints on processes of 
social life but the main thing for us is Ukraine with its 52 
million population. We will be guided by these considerations 
in the future," the Ukrainian president stressed. 
  Leonid Kravchuk expressed the hope for fruitful cooperation 
with the new head of the parliament. "If a man has no vanity but 
has self-control, his own stand and appropriate culture, it is 
always possible to find common ground with him," the Ukrainian 
president noted. 

</TEXT>

