<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cabinet Establishes Border Zone, Sets Restrictions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet Establishes Border Zone, Sets Restrictions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2005093494 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2005093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Cabinet of Ministers has adopted a resolution 
regarding the border zone. The zone is established along 
Ukraine's state land border, as well as along banks of border 
rivers and water reservoirs, within territories of settlements 
and village councils of people's deputies, which are adjacent to 
the border. 
  The resolution also approved general border regulations. In 
particular, they stipulate that citizens entering or staying 
within the border zone should have documents confirming their 
identity and need to enter the zone or remain there. Within the 
border zone, auto travel is limited, and a veterinary-sanitary 
zone is established, in which the breeding and grazing of 
livestock is prohibited. [passage indistinct] 

</TEXT>

