<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Economy Ministry Says Price Fluctuations Possible </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Economy Ministry Says Price Fluctuations Possible </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905153794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0945 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905153794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no date as received] -- The press service of 
Ukraine's Economy Ministry stated yesterday that reports of 
considerable consumer goods and services retail price and tariff 
rises, to be expected in May or June of this year, have appeared 
recently in some of the mass media. Interviews and statements 
on this are making purposeful references to a draft resolution 
that allegedly has already been drawn up by the ministry, the 
adoption of which would lead to a new round of inflation and a 
fall in the population's living standards. 
  The press service of Ukraine's Economy Ministry states in 
connection with this that no plan of general retail price and 
tariff rises has been developed. On the contrary, the 
government's moves to stabilize the economy have resulted in 
reducing inflation from 90 percent in December of last year to 
six percent in April of this year. Approximately the same level 
of inflation has been forecast for May. Of course, 
insignificant fluctuations in retail prices as a result of this 
or that factor are not ruled out. Ministry of Economy 
specialists expect, for example, that tariffs on city 
transportation services may rise, which will have to be approved 
by local authorities. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

