<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rukh Calls for Halt To Removal of Nuclear Weapons </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rukh Calls for Halt To Removal of Nuclear Weapons </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005022794 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2155 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005022794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Crimea, Kiev, 19 May -- "In conditions when the 
informational and organizational-parliamentary aggression by 
Russia in Crimea is being continued, we deem it necessary to 
stop the transfer of nuclear weapons from the territory of 
Ukraine," says the appeal of the People's Movement of Ukraine 
(Rukh). Further on the document states that the desire to drag 
through the Supreme Council of Crimea the Constitution of 6 May 
1992, separate citizenship of Crimea and the dual citizenship as 
well as the decision on liquidating the Ukrainian republican 
status of Sevastopol; the setting up of its own ministry of 
internal affairs and security service; the demands that the 
Sevastopol naval base should be transferred to the Russian Black 
Sea Fleet; the demands that the Ukrainian armed formations 
should be withdrawn from Crimea -- this is far from being the 
full list of the violations of the Constitution of Ukraine and 
Helsinki accords, and the illegitimate actions by the president 
and the Supreme Council of Crimea aimed at splitting Ukraine, 
igniting civil war and escalating conflict between Ukraine and 
Russia to the limit when its solution becomes possible only by 
means of armed struggle. 
  "All these actions by irresponsible helmsmen of Crimea are 
encouraged by the deputies to the State Duma of the Russian 
Federation with the president of Russia being aware of this. 
  "We demand that the world community should take resolute 
measures aimed at stopping the interference in the affairs of 
the sovereign Ukrainian state on the part of the government 
officials and the State Duma of Russia and guaranteeing security 
and territorial integrity of Ukraine. 
  "We demand that the Supreme Council and the president of 
Ukraine should take effective measures so that the Constitution 
and the laws of Ukraine be abided by in Crimea and that 
Ukraine's territorial integrity be ensured," says the appeal by 
Rukh. 

</TEXT>

