<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Official on Nuclear, Conventional Disarmament </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Official on Nuclear, Conventional Disarmament </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2005091594 Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network in 
Ukrainian 1400 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS2005091594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Ukrayinske Radio First Program Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Issues concerning supplies of modern weapons to the 
Ukrainian Armed Forces and use of the country's unique 
industrial and scientific-technical potential became the center 
of attention at a briefing held yesterday at the Ukrainian 
Defense Ministry. Lieutenant General Lev Hnatenko, first deputy 
chief of the Ukrainian Armed Forces Armaments and chief of the 
Armaments General Headquarters, spoke with journalists in detail 
about Ukraine's implementation of international agreements on 
nuclear disarmament and reduction of conventional weapons. He 
emphasized that, despite economic hardships, Ukraine is able, 
and should, produce military equipment which would be comparable 
to the world's best standards and become competitive on world 
markets. 
  Lt. Gen. Hnatenko also reported on certain problems of 
material provisions in the process of servicing already existing 
weapons. However, the main conclusion is that the Ukrainian 
Armed Forces is equipped with all necessary means to perform its 
tasks, which are aimed at protecting Ukraine's sovereignty and 
territorial integrity. 

</TEXT>

