<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rumors of Meeting on Russian Troops Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rumors of Meeting on Russian Troops Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944K1246B Baku BAKINSKIY RABOCHIY in Russian 17 May 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944K1246B </F>
<F P=104>  Baku BAKINSKIY RABOCHIY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> ["Announcement of Press Center of Ministry of Foreign </F>
Affairs of the Azerbaijan Republic"] 
  [Text] Certain press agencies, referring to the Press 
Center of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, are maintaining that 
on 13 May 1994 at the presidency of the Azerbaijan Republic 
there was a secret meeting at which opinions on the commitment 
of Russian troops to Azerbaijan were exchanged. It is maintained 
also that certain leading persons who took part in this meeting 
spoke for and against this matter. 
  The Press Center of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the 
Azerbaijan Republic deems it important to announce the following. 
  A meeting was held at the presidency of the Azerbaijan 
Republic on 13 May 1994. The military-political situation that 
has taken shape in the republic and ways out of it were 
discussed. The question of the commitment to Azerbaijan of 
troops of Russia or any other state was not discussed. 

</TEXT>

