<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kravchuk Promise Not To Use Force in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kravchuk Promise Not To Use Force in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005124294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1219 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005124294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 20 May (ITAR-TASS) -- Russian President 
Boris Yeltsin and Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk have given 
each other a promise not to adopt violent measures to resolve 
the "Crimean question." Boris Yeltsin told journalists this 
today during an interval between the presentation of credentials 
to the Russian president by the ambassadors of foreign states. 
  Boris Yeltsin referred to his telephone conversation 
yesterday with Leonid Kravchuk. Boris Yeltsin stressed in 
particular that the Crimea is a sovereign republic and is 
entitled to conduct its own policies. 

</TEXT>

