<H3> <TI>   Crimean President Says Situation Calm </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean President Says Situation Calm </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905192394 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1905192394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Thirty minutes ago we telephoned Crimean President 
Yuriy Meshkov and asked him to comment on the situation. 
  [Begin Meshkov recording] The situation in Crimea is calm. 
The attempts to influence our peace from outside are continuing 
with increasing intensity. The aim of these operations 
sanctioned by the present Kiev administration is to wreck the 
elections for Ukrainian president by provoking a conflict 
between Ukraine and the Republic of Crimea, and [word 
indistinct] the elimination of statehood and the executive 
authority structures in the hope that we will lose our nerve as 
a result of these provocations. We will respond, as Leonid 
Makarovich [Kravchuk] himself said, in a fitting way to your 
stupidity. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

