<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Welcomes Swedish Stand on Troops in Kaliningrad </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Welcomes Swedish Stand on Troops in Kaliningrad </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2005080294 Tallinn BNS in English 1914 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2005080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, May 19, BNS -- Lithuania welcomes Swedish 
Foreign Minister Margaretha af Ugglas' position that the number 
of Russian troops in the Kaliningrad region must be reduced, the 
Lithuanian Foreign Ministry said in a press release Thursday [19 
May]. 
  "The Kaliningrad region is an anomaly in the Baltic Sea 
region because of the huge army and navy forces concentrated in 
this area," af Ugglas was quoted as saying by the Lithuanian 
ministry. The Swedish minister, who visited the region 
Thursday, reportedly expressed hope that Russia will demonstrate 
its preparedness to reduce its military potential in Kaliningrad. 
  The Lithuanian ministry said efforts to raise the issue of 
Kaliningrad's demilitarization on an international level and to 
integrate the region into international cooperation processes 
would significantly contribute to enhancing security in the 
Baltic Sea region. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

