<F P=100> INTERREGIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Commander on Division of Black Sea Fleet </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Former Commander on Division of Black Sea Fleet </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105133394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1109 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105133394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 21 TASS -- Marshal Yevgeniy 
Shaposhnikov, former commander-in-chief of the allied armed 
forces of the Commonwealth of Independent States, believes that 
the Black Sea Fleet should be divided between all the countries 
of the Commonwealth of Independent States (CIS) rather than 
between Russia and Ukraine. 
  Expressing his private opinion in a speech over Russian 
television on Saturday, he said that, since Ukraine did not join 
the CIS Treaty on Collective Security, it should be given 
one-eleventh part of the fleet. 
  The rest of the fleet should be used to protect the CIS 
interests in the Black Sea area. 
  Shaposhnikov also suggested that if any CIS country is 
unable 
to finance its part of the fleet, it can hand it over under the 
control of any other CIS country and receive for it a 
compensation in the form of oil, coal and other minerals. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

