<F P=106> [BELINFORM-TASS report: "Will the Ruble Come to </F>
Belorussia?"] 
  [Text] Whether the Treaty on Monetary Union with Russia 
goes ahead or not now depends on the results of Belorussia's 
[Belarus'] presidential election, Vyacheslav Kebich, chairman of 
the Republic's Council of Ministers, told a public meeting in 
Grodno Oblast. 
  He also stressed that "this is not so much monetary union as 
economic union, and it is being signed not for two or three 
months but for centuries to come. I am confident that this 
union will go ahead, just as I am confident that Ukraine will 
also join it." According to the prime minister, in the near 
future Tajikistan will also state that it is joining the 
economic union. 

</TEXT>

