<H3> <TI>   Military Talks on Cooperation With Russia End in Minsk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Military Talks on Cooperation With Russia End in Minsk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2305094294 Minsk BELAPAN in Belarusian 1400 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2305094294 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk BELAPAN </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A two-day working meeting of Russian and Belarusian 
military delegations has ended in Minsk. The delegations 
prepared agreements on bilateral cooperation. In particular, 
they discussed procedures for financing military formations of 
strategic forces, which are temporarily deployed on Belarusian 
territory, as well as those for using Russia's firing ranges by 
formations and units of the Belarusian Air Defense. The Russian 
delegation was headed by Ambassador at Large Veniyamin Popov, 
while its military section was headed by Colonel General 
Gennadiy Gichkin, deputy chief of the General Staff of Russia's 
Armed Forces. The Belarusian delegation was headed by 
Lieutenant General Mikalay Churkin, chief of the General Staff 
of the Belarusian Armed Forces. 

</TEXT>

