  [Text] As we have already informed, a Belarusian military 
delegation headed by Defense Minister Pavel Kazlowski paid a 
one-day working visit to Lithuania on 19 May. The delegation 
held meetings with Seimas [parliament] Chairman C. Jursenas and 
Defense Minister L. Linkevicius. According to our correspondent 
in Vilnius, it was resolved to create working groups of both 
states for preparing documents on cooperation between the 
Lithuanian and Belarusian Ministries of Defense. During the 
news conference, held at the Lithuanian Seimas at the end of the 
visit, L. Linkevicius stated that the meeting with P. Kazlowski 
was devoted to issues related to the formation of a structure of 
both states' defense systems and other common problems. 
"Notwithstanding the fact that Belarus participates in the CIS 
collective system of security, there were no barriers to a 
normal dialogue," Linkevicius said. 

