<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Secret Document Reveals Plans To Establish Russian Enclave </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Secret Document Reveals Plans To Establish Russian Enclave </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2005110794 Kiev NARODNA HAZETA in Ukrainian No. 21 (152) 
May 94 p 5 </F>

<F P=103> AU2005110794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev NARODNA HAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "We Will Have a Dangerous Neighbor"] </F>
  [Text] The Press Service of the organization "Ukraine's 
State Independence" has got hold of a document under the title 
"A Special Status for the Dniester Region (Considerations on 
Possible Legal Foundations)," which had been compiled by a 
"plenipotentiary representative of the president of the Russian 
Federation to the negotiations on the political settlement of 
the conflict in the Moldovan Republic's Dniester Region." 
Russia proposes that "a special status" for the Dniester Region 
be established by means of which Russia could actively influence 
Moldova's domestic and external policy. In accordance with the 
document handed over to the Moldovan side for consideration, the 
elected legislative body of the Dniester Region "may suspend the 
action on its territory of laws and normative acts of the 
Moldovan Republic, if they are at variance with the special 
status...." (Section 7). Thus, a foreign state grants a regular 
administrative region of sovereign Moldova the status of a fully 
autonomous enclave. The 10 sections of the Russian project are 
aimed at creating a separate state, which will be Moscow's 
vassal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

