<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shooting Continues in N. Ossetian Emergency Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shooting Continues in N. Ossetian Emergency Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105203294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1919 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz May 21 TASS -- The situation in parts of 
north Ossetia under the state of emergency remains tense, 
according to reports from military sources. 
  Shooting broke out five times in the Prigorod district last 
night. On the whole, the situation is under control of the 
Russian army and local law enforcement bodies. 
  Head of the temporary administration Vladimir Lozovoy said 
in 
his address to the population that "attacks on civilians and 
police and army check points and hostage taking continue in the 
zone of the state of emergency. It is outrageous when members 
of local administrations become organisers of and accomplices in 
unlawful actions. Heads of bodies of power and power structures 
who are unable or unwilling to carry out their duties to ensure 
law and order will be called to account. I call on the citizens 
of North Ossetia and Ingushetia to resist provocations of 
extremists who use any means to thwart the settlement of the 
conflict." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

