<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chechnya Celebrates `Caucasian War' Anniversary </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chechnya Celebrates `Caucasian War' Anniversary </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105132894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1255 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105132894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sharip Asuev] </F>
  [Text] Groznyy (Chechnya) May 21 TASS -- The Chechen 
Republic marked the 130th anniversary since the end of the 
Caucasian war with a parade of the best units of the emerging 
Chechen army in its capital city Groznyy on Saturday. 
  Dzhokhar Dudayev, republican president and 
commander-in-chief 
of armed forces, presented banners and standards with Chechen 
symbols to 12 regular units before the parade. 
  A conference devoted to the anniversary since the end of the 
50-year-long war of tsarist Russia against highlanders, was also 
held in the Chechen capital on the same day. 
  Its participants, including guests from Saudi Arabia, the 
United States and Jordan, noted that the Russian empire 
conquered Caucasian peoples with fire and sword but could not 
suppress their will for freedom. 
  Addressing the conference, Dudayev called for "establishing 
an international tribunal to condemn the continued colonial 
policy of Russia in the Caucasus". 

</TEXT>

