  [Text] The material damage caused by the explosions at the 
Pacific Fleet's aviation depot 14-15 May near the village of 
Novonezhino has reached approximately 31 billion rubles. This 
sum does not include losses incurred by the military, stated 
(Svetlana Parinova), chairwoman of the economy and planning 
committee of the Maritime kray administration, speaking at a 
conference in Vladivostok devoted to measures to clear up the 
aftermath of the blast. Many of the Maritime kray's commercial 
structures have expressed their willingness to provide those 
affected with material help, INTERFAX notes. 

