<H3> <TI>   Rostov-Na-Donu Stops Presses on Moscow Newspapers </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rostov-Na-Donu Stops Presses on Moscow Newspapers </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK2005132994 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 20 May 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK2005132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Anatoliy Borovkov report under the "News From the Regions" </F>
rubric: "Fate Crushes Down on Central Newspapers in the Shape 
of `Molot'"] 
  [Text] Rostov-na-Donu -- Many subscribers to central 
newspapers in Rostov Oblast have been left without their 
favorite periodicals. "Molot," the biggest publishing house in 
Russia's South, has discontinued printing such newspapers as 
ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI, RABOCHAYA TRIBUNA, ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA, and 
SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA. Awaiting their turn are GUDOK, SOVETSKIY 
SPORT, and SPORT-EKSPRESS. The reason is the one that has grown 
to be banal: The newspapers cannot pay their newsprint and 
printing debts. 

</TEXT>

