<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Roads and Communications Minister Andi Meister, 
Interior Minister Heiki Arike, and Population Minister Peeter 
Olesk have stated that they will continue work in the government 
on the basis of the [1992] coalition agreement. These ERSP 
[Estonian National Independence Party] ministers said in a 
statement which they sent to the radio that they understand the 
need to prevent a power vacuum at a critical time for the state 
of Estonia. They made this decision taking into account the 
positions expressed at the joint meeting of the ERSP board and 
its Riigikogu faction. 

