<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Delegation Visits </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Delegation Visits </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005162894 Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network in Estonian 1200 
GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005162894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn Radio Tallinn Network </F>
<F P=105>  Estonian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An Estonian Foreign Ministry delegation is on a tour 
to the countries in the Caucasus this week. On 17 May, Foreign 
Ministry Deputy Chancellor Raul Malk and Azerbaijani Deputy 
Foreign Minister Albert Salamnov signed an agreement on 
consultations between the two countries' foreign ministries. 
The Estonian delegation also met Azerbaijani Trade Minister 
Ridvan Huseynov and . discussed with him prospects for trade 
between the two countries. 
  Since 18 May, the delegation has been holding talks in 
Georgia. During the [word indistinct] discussions at the 
Georgian Foreign Ministry, both countries' topical foreign 
policy issues were discussed including the international aspects 
of the Abkhaz conflict and the Russian troop withdrawal from 
Estonia. Georgian Foreign Minister Aleksandre Chikvaidze and 
Estonian Foreign Ministry Deputy Chancellor Raul Malk signed an 
agreement on cooperation between the two countries' foreign 
policy departments. Today, the Estonian delegation will be 
meeting Georgian leader Eduard Shevardnadze. In the afternoon, 
the delegation will leave Tbilisi for Yerevan where an agreement 
on cooperation between the foreign ministries is due to be 
signed. 

</TEXT>

