<F P=100> Lithuania </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Adopts Law Increasing Number of Ministries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Adopts Law Increasing Number of Ministries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS2005114694 Tallinn BNS in English 1029 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS2005114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vilnius, May 20, BNS -- The Lithuanian parliament 
on Thursday [19 May] passed the law on government which provides 
for 19 ministries instead of the present 16. The parliament 
voted 49-43 and 3 lawmakers abstained. 
  Lithuania will have a new Administration Reforms and 
Municipal Affairs Ministry and an Environment Protection 
Ministry. The presently existing Ministry of Culture and 
Education will be divided into two separate institutions. 
  The new law also provides for ministers without portfolio 
whose functions and authorizations will be defined by the prime 
minister. 

</TEXT>

