<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 23 TASS -- The Russian prime minister is 
holding an emergency conference on the latest developments in 
the Crimea, the press service of the Russian Government informed 
ITAR- TASS. 
  The press service has been unable to specify when Russian- 
Ukrainian negotiations on the subject at the prime ministerial 
level will begin today. 
  The political situation in the Crimea has been growing 
increasingly tense since the Crimean Parliament passed a law to 
restore the constitution of the Republic of Crimea adopted on 
May 6, 1992. The constitution provides for greater independence 
of the peninsula in relations with Ukraine. 
  Kiev regards this move as a manifestation of separatism and 
a 
threat to Ukraine's territorial integrity. 

