<H3> <TI>   Calls Situation `Potentially Explosive' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls Situation `Potentially Explosive' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005200994 Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network in Russian 1700 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005200994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Ostankino Television First Channel 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Novosti" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev regards the 
concentration of Ukrainian troops in Crimea as potentially 
explosive. According to the information coming in, the defense 
minister said, about 400 Ukrainian special purpose troops are 
concentrated in the airport area near Simferopol. Five hundred 
Ukrainian servicemen have been deployed at the Cape of Khersones 
and, in the area of Sukhaya Bolka, on the eastern outskirts of 
Sevastopol--200 servicemen. When troops are being brought in 
and concentrated in an area, Pavel Grachev said, they can start 
military activities at any moment. The minister gave assurances 
that he had given the order for decisive action to stop all 
provocations directed against the Black Sea Fleet, regardless of 
who commits them. 

</TEXT>

