<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister Views Ukrainian `Provocation' in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister Views Ukrainian `Provocation' in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305080994 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0435 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Mikhail Shevtsov and Andrey </F>
Palariya] 
  [Text] Moscow, 23 May -- This morning Internal Affairs 
Minister Valeriy Kuzentsov announced that the situation in 
Crimea is being monitored. At the same time, he said, yesterday 
the Ukrainian minister of internal affairs sent all town and 
rayon departments telegrams with orders to obey instructions 
from Kiev only. Valeriy Kuznetsov assessed this step by the 
Ukrainian leadership as a provocation aimed at destabilizing the 
situation on the peninsula. 
  The duty officer of the Black Sea Fleet staff told TASS 
that, 
following the completion of routine exercise, all units and 
subunits of the fleet are in their permanent places of 
deployment. They are not carrying out any maneuvers at present. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

