<H3> <TI>   LDPR Protests Against Ukraine `Attack' in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    LDPR Protests Against Ukraine `Attack' in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005205394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1815 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Vladimir Zhirinovskiy's nationalist Liberal 
Democratic Party of Russia (LDPR) has expressed indignation over 
Ukrainian troops' "attack on the building of the Interior 
Ministry of (Ukrainian autonomous republic of) Crimea in order 
to change it into a so-called Central Department for Crimea of 
the Interior Ministry of Ukraine." 
  "Your government, Mr. Kravchuk, has already plundered 
Ukraine 
and run down what was a rich land," the LDPR says in a statement 
received by Interfax on Friday. "Now it is stealing Russian and 
Turkmen gas and oil transported through your territory." 
  Kravchuk "wishes to sell the Black Sea Fleet (disputed by 
Russia and Ukraine) for scrap metal, to sell everything that can 
be sold, in order to flee the devastated country when its people 
rise and demand reunification with Russia," the party says. 

</TEXT>

