<H3> <TI>   Baltic Fleet To Take Part in NATO Naval Exercise </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Baltic Fleet To Take Part in NATO Naval Exercise </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305103294 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0600 
GMT 23 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Biryukov] </F>
  [Text] Kaliningrad, 23 May -- Warships from the fleets of 
the Baltic countries have been invited to the first phase of the 
NATO "Baltops-94" joint naval maneuvers. Russia's Baltic fleet 
will be represented by the guided missile destroyer 
Neustrashimyy, whose crew will take part in working out combined 
sailing tasks, in demonstration submarine-hunting operations, 
helicopter landings of inspection groups, and search and rescue 
at sea. This stage will be under way from 7-10 June. More than 
40 ships and combat craft, three submarines, and naval aviation 
from 12 countries will be taking part in combat tasks in the 
southern Baltic. 

