<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Calls for International Conference on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Calls for International Conference on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM2305092994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 21 May 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM2305092994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation Federal Assembly State Duma Appeal "in </F>
Connection with the Situation on the Territory of the Former 
Yugoslavia"] 
  [Text] Moscow, 13 May 1994 -- The Russian Federation 
Federal Assembly State Duma believes that in the situation which 
has taken shape a real opportunity has appeared for establishing 
peace on the territory of the former Yugoslavia. 
  In this connection the State Duma appeals to all sides 
taking 
part in the conflict to cease all hostilities immediately and to 
embark on talks to establish peace. For its part the State Duma 
is prepared to render all-around assistance to set up dialogue 
between the sides involved. 
  The State Duma appeals to all parliaments of the world to 
prevent decisions which could destabilize the situation in the 
former Yugoslavia and primarily those leading to the violation 
of the embargo on arms supplies to any of the warring sides. 
  The State Duma suggests that the parliaments of states 
adjacent to the territory of the former Yugoslavia hold an 
international conference with the participation of UN and CSCE 
representatives on ways of overcoming the crisis in the Balkans. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

