<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source': Russia Does Not Sell Weapons to North Korea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Source': Russia Does Not Sell Weapons to North Korea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305110694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1035 GMT 23 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2305110694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Vladimir Solntsev] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 23 TASS -- Russia is not selling weapons 
to North Korea at present, but has the right to do so as no 
international sanctions have been imposed on Pyongyang. 
  "At present there are no international sanctions against the 
People's Democratic Republic of Korea. Therefore, Russia, as 
any other country, has the right to ship to North Korea purely 
defensive systems of armaments and spare parts to them on a 
commercial basis", a high-ranking government source told TASS on 
Monday. 
  Pyongyang's foreign debt to Moscow, which remains from the 
time of the former Soviet Union, exceeds three billion US 
dollars and impedes commercial operations with North Korea, 
according to the source. 

</TEXT>

