will to do that. 
  [K. Zatulin, chairman of State Duma committee for CIS 
affairs] Alexander Dumas the elder commented that blood in the 
south flows more quickly, thus any indigent nobleman from the 
south of France, from Gascogne, who went to Paris would make a 
career for himself faster than his far richer comrade from the 
north, from Normandie or Picardie. I think that what goes for 
France is typical for the south of Russia, too. [end recording] 

