<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Expresses Confidence in Interior Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Expresses Confidence in Interior Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005133494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1313 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- The recent murder of State 
Duma deputy and member of the new Regional Policy faction Andrey 
Aizderdzis provoked indignation of Russian political circles and 
President Boris Yeltsin, says a statement of Presidential Press 
Secretary Vyacheslav Kostikov. 
  A number of State Duma factions even suggested to remove 
Interior Minister Viktor Yerin from his post. 
  The president has studied the investigation materials, 
motives and circumstances of the murder. In his opinion, the 
Interior Ministry acted swiftly and professionally. The 
ministry's measures against crime and corruption have improved 
as well. 
  Vyacheslav Kostikov was authorized to state that the 
president see no reasons for disciplinary measures as regards 
Viktor Yerin and has full confidence in the Interior Ministry. 
  "He is confident of competence, high professional and 
personal qualities of Viktor Yerin. The question of Yerin's 
removal from his post will not be raised," says the statement. 

</TEXT>

