<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Boris Yeltsin has no reason to distrust or 
punish his Interior Minister Viktor Yerin, presidential 
spokesman Vyacheslav Kostikov said in a statement issued in 
Moscow on Friday. This follows a proposal from a number of 
parliamentary factions that the minister be dismissed following 
the recent assassination of Russian deputy Andrey Aizderdzis. 
  The president has examined materials related to the case and 
thinks the ministry's actions to be prompt and impeccable, the 
statement says. It also quotes Yeltsin as saying there has been 
certain progress in the ministry's campaign against crime and 
corruption. 
  The spokesman said the question of Yerin's dismissal was not 
on the agenda. 

