<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Rybkin Discuss Social Accord Treaty </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Rybkin Discuss Social Accord Treaty </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005143294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1348 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin and Speaker of the Russian parliament lower house Ivan 
Rybkin who met in the Kremlin on Friday, examined the political 
situation in the country, following the singing of the Treaty of 
Civic Accord. 
  According to Presidential Press Secretary Vyacheslav 
Kostikov, the sides noted that concerted actions by the 
president and the lower house to gain political stabilisation 
yielded positive results. 
  They examined versions of conciliation procedures to 
implement the treaty in the spirit of a constructive dialogue. 
  The president and the speaker also discussed the formation 
of 
the federal budget. They pointed to the similarity of 
approaches to the adjustment of the budget's military section, 
taking into account real requirements of the army and social 
needs of servicemen. 
  Rybkin informed Yeltsin about the debates at the lower house 
of a bill on the Constitutional Court and a commission on 
constitutional amendments. In this connection, they discussed 
personnel issues. 
  The president and the speaker analysed the political results 
of their latest trips -- to Germany and China, respectively. 

</TEXT>

