<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Yeltsin-Rybkin Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Yeltsin-Rybkin Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005172094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1600 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005172094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- A difficult situation which 
developed in the Russian economy was the major issue of the 
meeting between Russian President Boris Yeltsin and Chairman of 
the Lower House of the Russian Parliament Ivan Rybkin. 
  Upon completion of the meeting Rybkin informed lawmakers of 
the State Duma about its results. Rybkin pointed out that the 
two discussed problems connected with insolvency in industry and 
measures for the prevention of further production decline. 
  Rybkin said that they discussed measures to be taken by the 
State Duma to give a legislative support to the Treaty of Civic 
Accord. 
  Much attention was given to the budget-94 draft law which 
will be discussed by the State Duma in the second reading and in 
particular, to articles of the draft law concerning needs of the 
Army, education, culture and science. 
  Rybkin said that he had informed the Russian president that 
a 
presidential decree and a resolution of the Russian Government, 
under which a block of buildings in the Okhotny Ryad Street were 
transferred to the State Duma, were not fulfilled by some 
organisations which had not moved out from the building given to 
the State Duma as its new residence. Rybkin voiced satisfaction 
that after his conversation with the Russian president all 
organisations ignoring the resolution were given a strict 
warning to move out until May 26. 

</TEXT>

