<H3> <TI>   Khasbulatov Quits Politics, Returns to Academic Work </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Khasbulatov Quits Politics, Returns to Academic Work </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105191794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1840 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105191794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Mikhail Karlov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 21 TASS -- Former Russian Parliament 
Chairman Ruslan Khasbulatov has confirmed his intention to quit 
politics and fully devote himself to science. 
  In his recent interview with ITAR-TASS in Groznyy where he 
moved after his release from prison in February 1993, 
Khasbulatov said that he will return to his academic work at the 
Russian Academy of Economics. 
  One of the academy leaders said that Khasbulatov has been in 
charge of the Department of Foreign Economic Relations for two 
weeks. 

</TEXT>

