<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tamara Zamyatina] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- Economic measures designed to 
combat the crisis in Russia were discussed by President Yeltsin 
and the State Duma speaker during their meeting in the Kremlin 
today, the Russian president told journalists. 
  According to Yeltsin his conversation with Ivan Rybkin 
carried on the four-hour discussion the president had with 
industrialists and entrepreneurs on Thursday concerning a 
package of presidential decrees on economic reform which are 
being prepared now. 
  Yeltsin stressed that the press misrepresented his statement 
on the possible collapse of the economy on Thursday. "The 
collapse may occur if we do not take steps to overcome the 
crisis. We must make all efforts not to let the worst to 
happen," the president said. 

</TEXT>

