<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chernomyrdin Details Economic Situation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chernomyrdin Details Economic Situation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005165894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1459 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005165894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Gennadiy Yezhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 20 TASS -- Russia has her own way of 
entering the market, her own model of development, announced 
Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin on Thursday at a meeting with 
the heads of enterprises and organisations in the spheres of 
industry, construction and transportation. The meeting was held 
immediately after another signing ceremony during which business 
and organisation heads affixed their names to the Treaty on 
Social Accord. 
  Chernomyrdin stressed that the treaty is a historically 
important document which creates the conditions for the 
stabilisation of Russia's political and economic life. Russia 
is paying a steep price for reforms, the premier noted, and gave 
a detailed account of the economic situation in the country. 
  The prime minister declared that the government's number one 
task was to keep spending within the parameters of the budget. 
A series of presidential decrees and governmental resolutions 
have already been prepared with the goal of improving the 
economic situation and strengthening the Policy of Social 
Accord. These steps are designed to "redirect the restructuring 
of the economy in favor of the domestic producer", he said. 
  The premier reffered, in particular, to the lowering of 
several tax rates this year, to the cancellation of taxes on 
investments, to the significant lowering of customs duties on 
oil, gas, aluminum, pulp and the other main components of the 
Russian export, as well as the cancellation of quotas and 
mandatory licensing for exports. This summer will already 
witness the lowering of the amount companies are required to put 
into the social security fund, which is one form of taxes. As 
the government implements its plan to sharply improve the 
efficiency of the tax-collecting agencies, it hopes to be able 
to reduce the over-all tax load by 10 to 20 per cent next year. 
  According to Chernomyrdin, the government envisions 
requiring 
banks to report the opening of an account by a firm, and also 
taking additional measures on debt circulation, including the 
possibility of extinguising the debts of unviable enterprises by 
confiscating their property. 
  The premier especially pointed out the necessity of 
strengthening executive discipline on every level. "Without 
discipline we will not be able to do anything in this country", 
he emphasized. 
  He said that regulatory measures would be adopted to 
decrease 
the salary gap in various sectors of the economy, including in 
the government. 

</TEXT>

