<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Social Policy for Improving Living Standard Approved </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Social Policy for Improving Living Standard Approved </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105180594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1726 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow May 21 TASS -- The Russian Government 
adopted on Saturday main guidelines of social policy in 1994 
aimed at stabilisation and gradual improvement of living 
standards in Russia. 
  The document signed by Prime Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin 
obliges all federal executive bodies to draw up their programmes 
of targeted social assistance and wage increases on these 
guidelines. 
  They call in particular for measures to stop further 
decreases of wages and salaries, balance economic interests and 
material possibilities of three major categories of the 
population -- employees, entrepreneurs and disabled people, 
reform the social sphere and increase the role of the state in 
employment and retraining of citizens. 
  The document also envisages establishing efficient private 
ownership of housing and preservation of housing subsidies for 
lower income families. 

</TEXT>

