<H3> <TI>   World Bank Agrees $200 Million Loan for Banks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    World Bank Agrees $200 Million Loan for Banks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005090394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0730 GMT 20 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005090394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Worl Bank's Board of Directors approved a loan 
of $200 million to Russia. The statement from the major 
international credit and financial organization says that these 
funds will be directed to giving technical assistance to private 
banks and to helping Russia's Central Bank to train inspectors 
and to create a system of early discovery of problem banks. The 
European Bank of Reconstruction and Development, the European 
Community, and private investors will also take part in 
financing this program. 
  The $200 million is being granted to Russia for a term of 17 
years. No payments need to be made on it for the first five 
years. 

</TEXT>

