<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Progress M-23 Spacecraft Launched </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Progress M-23 Spacecraft Launched </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205075694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0720 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2205075694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 22 TASS -- A Progress M-23 cargo 
spacecraft, launched from Baykonur Cosmodrome at seven hours 30 
minutes 02 seconds, Moscow daylight saving time, on Sunday, was 
put into orbit with the following parameters: 
  -- Maximum distance from the Earth surface -- 247 km, 
  -- minimum distance from the Earth surface -- 192 km, 
  -- orbital period -- 88.6 minutes, 
  -- orbital inclination -- 51.6 degrees. 
  The onboard systems of the spacecraft are functioning 
properly. 
  The spacecraft is to deliver 2,207 kilogrammes of various 
cargoes to the orbital station Mir. The two spacecrafts are to 
dock on May 24. 

</TEXT>

