<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Reportedly Violating Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijan Reportedly Violating Cease-Fire </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC2005171494 Yerevan Radio Yerevan in Azeri 1330 GMT 20 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2005171494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan Radio Yerevan </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The opposing sides in the Nagorno-Karabakh front 
line have refrained from launching intensive combat operations. 
However, the Nagorno-Karabakh Republic [NKR] Defense Army Press 
Service has disclosed that over the past few days Azerbaijan has 
violated the relatively peaceful situation. That republic's 
military forces have been firing on the NKR defense positions. 
For example, this morning Azerbaijani units fired on the NKR 
positions in the northeastern part of the confrontation lines 
with mortars. The Armenian side remains committed to the 
cease-fire agreement and has held back from returning the fire. 
  Meanwhile, the Armenian Ministry of Defense Press Service 
has 
disclosed that the relatively peaceful situation in the 
northeastern part of Armenia was disrupted again yesterday. The 
defense positions around Vagashen in Idzhevanskiy Rayon were 
fired on with infantry combat vehicles at 1405. No one was hurt. 
  The same source also noted that no other incidents occurred 
on Armenia's border last night and this morning. 

</TEXT>

