  [Text] Stepanakert ("LRAGIR", "AZG" dailies), 05/20/94 -- 
There have been no serious changes at the Karabakh fronts for a 
week. The sides are refraining from active military operations. 
Nevertheless, the Azeris continue shelling the Armenian defense 
positions at different sections of the front. 
  The RMK [Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] Defense Army 
Headquarters report, the enemy shelled the Karabakh positions at 
the villages of Seisulan, Karmiravan, Gasangaya and Levonarkh in 
the Mardakertskiy district in the morning of May 19. No 
casualties are reported. 
  Two hours later, the Azeri armored personnel carriers 
shelled 
the Karabakh positions at the villages of Bashkyarvend, Gyuluja, 
Suma and Umudlu in the Agdamskiy district. Again, no casualties 
are reported. Meanwhile, the enemy shelled the Karabakh 
positions at the Umar gorge and at the villages of Karakanbeyli 
and Kurgan. 
  At 6pm the enemy shelled, using large caliber machine guns, 
the Armenian positions at the village of Giulistan in the 
Shaumyaninskiy district. 

</TEXT>

