agreement on establishing an Association "Crimea-Armenia Trade 
House" was reached between Industry Minister Ashot Safaryan and 
President Yuri Meshkov. The Association will have offices in 
Yerevan and Simferopol. 
  During the Armenian minister's to Crimea [as received], the 
sides discussed questions of mutual airports granting for 
transit flights and using Crimean ports for shipment to Armenia. 
  The Armenian side expressed her readiness to take part in 
the 
state program of Armenians' return to Crimea, deported 50 years 
ago. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

