<H3> <TI>   Abkhazians Reportedly Concentrating Troops in Gali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Abkhazians Reportedly Concentrating Troops in Gali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005193594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1815 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Interfax learned Friday at the press center of the 
Georgian Defense Ministry that more than 500 Abkhaz fighters 
were concentrated in the Gali region. The number is constantly 
increasing. There is also a high concentration of military 
technology. The center reported it had evidence to show that in 
the night of May 20-21 Abkhazia was planning wide scale 
operations to put an end to the peace talks and provoke a new 
escalation of the conflict. 
  The Georgian Defense Ministry calls on the leaders of Abkhaz 
armed formations to withhold from any military actions which 
could lead to renewed bloodshed. 

</TEXT>

