<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Situation Remains Stable </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Situation Remains Stable </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105080794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0718 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Dzyublo] </F>
  [Text] Moscow May 21 TASS -- The situation in the Galskiy 
District where, according to the Georgian Defence Ministry, 
concentration of Abkhazian troops was registered on Friday, has 
not changed, Georgian Defence Minister Vardiko Nadibaidze said 
in an exclusive telephone interview with ITAR-TASS on Saturday. 
  According to the minister, the situation "is closely 
monitored", and no additional massing of troops and combat 
materiel was registered. 
  As the Georgian Defence Minstry reported earlier, the 
concentration of armed groups numbering over 500 and an increase 
in combat materiel were registered in the upper zone of the 
Galskiy District on Friday. 
  However, apprehensions about "a planned large-scale 
operation" have not been confirmed so far. 

</TEXT>

