<H3> <TI>   Troops Not Seen as Guarantor of Refugees' Return </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Troops Not Seen as Guarantor of Refugees' Return </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005141194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1101 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005141194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Tengiz Pachkoriya] </F>
  [Text] Tbilisi May 20 TASS -- More than 62 per cent of 
Georgian residents surveyed recently by the newspaper SVOBODNAYA 
GRUZIA (FREE GEORGIA) answered negatively when asked if they 
considered the Russian-dominated CIS peace-keeping troops a 
reliable guarantee of the safe return of refugees to Abkhazia. 
  The newspaper's survey, published on Friday, had the goal of 
determining Georgian society's opinion of the four-sided 
agreement on a ceasefire and withdrawal of forces, which was 
signed in Moscow on May 14. Twenty per cent of the inhabitants 
of Tbilisi and Georgia answered positively to the above 
question, while about 15 per cent did not express an opinion. 

</TEXT>

