<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia, Georgia To Settle Border, Customs Problems </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia, Georgia To Settle Border, Customs Problems </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205140894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1309 GMT 22 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2205140894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia and Georgia have concentrated on settling 
border and customs problems. Chairman of Georgia's Border 
Department Viktor Lordkipanidze told Interfax that a special 
Georgian commission was set up to demarcate the border between 
Russia and Georgia. 
  He also announced that the economic border with customs 
offices was to be defined next week. The Georgian customs 
office will be located in Gantiadi and the Russian one in Adler. 
The motorway customs offices will be located in Gantiadi, Roki, 
Mamisoni and Kazbegi (Georgia) and in Adler, Nizhni Zaramag and 
Verkhny Lars (Russia). 
  Lordkipanidze also said that talks were underway on the 
demarcation of the state border. The final variant will be 
chosen with due account taken of both countries' interests, he 
said. 
  He said that the customs offices would be opened in the near 
future, perhaps earlier than a political decision on the issue 
would be taken. 

</TEXT>

