<F P=103> LD2105152094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The border villages of the Kazakh region in the 
northwest of Azerbaijan came under "intensive fire" from guns 
and tanks from the side of the Armenian village of Voskepar on 
Friday night, the press service of the Azeri Defense Ministry 
reported. 
  The shelling inflicted damage to the villages of 
Gushchu-Airym and Mazam. Several civilians were wounded. 
  Also on Saturday the village of Sadarak and the border strip 
of the Shakhbuzsky region of the Nakhichevan autonomous republic 
were shelled from the Armenian territory. 
  According to the Azeri Defense Ministry, "Armenian troops 
carry out planned destruction of houses, communications, 
historical monuments in the city of Agdam and a number of seized 
villages of the Agdam region." 

</TEXT>

