<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Says Russian Troops Not To Be Called In </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Says Russian Troops Not To Be Called In </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205195694 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1800 GMT 22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205195694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian Federation troops will not be brought into 
Azerbaijan, President Geydar Aliyev of Azerbaijan has declared. 
He denied opposition accusations that the country might lose 
its sovereignty. According to Aliyev, political parties should 
consult and interact with the official bodies instead of holding 
rallies and mass protest actions. The Azerbaijani leader 
reiterated that the authorities acted correctly in signing the 
Bishkek protocol on a cease-fire. 
  Meanwhile, the situation in the conflict zone remains 
relatively calm. The Azerbaijani Defense Ministry reports only 
rare cases of shelling of its territory from Armenia. 
  The headquarters of the Azerbaijani National Independence 
Party has been raided. The premises were blockaded by 200 
policemen, who announced they intended to find weapons. 
However, the press service of the republican Interior Ministry 
refuses to comment on this report, saying it knows nothing about 
the incident. 

