<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin, Kravchuk Discuss Crimea Over Telephone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin, Kravchuk Discuss Crimea Over Telephone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1905132294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1304 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1905132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM for TASS] </F>
  [Text] Kiev 19 May TASS -- Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk and Russian President Boris Yeltsin had a telephone 
conversation on Thursday [19 May]. 
  The Ukrainian president's press service reported that the 
presidents had a frank exchange of opinions on speeding up the 
implementation of the Ukrainian-Russian arrangements reached at 
the Moscow meeting on April 15. 
  They agreed that the problems should be discussed in the 
next 
few days at the level of heads of governments for the subsequent 
signing of the documents by the Ukrainian and Russian presidents. 
  Kravchuk and Yeltsin also touched upon the situation in the 
Crimea. Kravchuk spelled out his position on settling the 
Crimean problem in the framework of the constitutional regime. 
  He stressed that Ukraine would take appropriate measures to 
preserve territorial integrity of the state. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

