<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fleet Exercises End; 50,000 Troops Said in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fleet Exercises End; 50,000 Troops Said in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2305081394 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 0730 GMT 23 
May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2305081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow 2x2 Television </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpts] The largest Black Sea Fleet exercises for some 
time have ended in the Crimea. Approximately 30 ships, coastal 
units, and aviation took part. Subunits and ships are now in 
their usual places of deployment and there are no troop 
movements. The maneuvers demonstrated the fleet's high degree 
of combat readiness. [passage omitted] 
  On the whole the situation remains calm throughout the 
peninsula, but according to the latest figures there are now 
approximately 50,000 Ukrainian soldiers in Crimea, and their 
number continues to increase. Mainly they are special purpose 
units. 

</TEXT>

