<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk, U.S. Financier Discuss Further Aid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk, U.S. Financier Discuss Further Aid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005183194 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005183194 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, Ukraine's President Leonid Kravchuk received 
George Soros, a well-known financier, [word indistinct] and U.S. 
public figure. There was a conversation, a significant part of 
which was held in the absence of press representatives. Various 
aspects of further aid to Ukraine on the part of the Soros 
Foundation were discussed during the conversation. 
  Leonid Kravchuk emphasized that in our state they highly 
assess the humanistic activity of this foundation and are 
grateful for the aid that is so necessary today for the 
Ukrainian state. 
  After the conversation George Soros granted an interview to 
journalists in which he, in particular, emphasized that during 
his meeting with the president, apart from stating positive 
factors of cooperation with our state, they also discussed an 
issue on exempting from taxation separate kinds of aid extended 
by the Soros Foundation to Ukraine. This will significantly 
expand the possibilities of its activities in Ukraine. 

</TEXT>

