<H3> <TI>   Saburov More Interested in Sewerage System Than Crisis </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Saburov More Interested in Sewerage System Than Crisis </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005182594 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005182594 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
BFN 

    [Editorial Report] Moscow Russian Television Network in 
Russian at 1625 GMT on 20 May broadcast the regular "Details" 
program presented by Sergey Dorenko, which was devoted to a 
nine-minute video report by correspondent Vladislav 
Flyarkovskiy. Before introducing this report, Dorenko briefly 
commented on the Crimean crisis, saying: 
  "The Crimean Supreme Soviet today restored the peninsula's 
Constitution, a highly autonomous Constitution, and everyone was 
expecting a response from Kiev and possible clashes. But the 
day passed off without clashes. We spoke to Crimean Prime 
Minister Yevgeniy Saburov over the telephone and he, in contrast 
to us, said that he was more interested in the problem of 
Crimea's sewerage system, and that he did not share our fears 
today." 

</TEXT>

