1800 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Ukrainian Supreme Council set up a working 
commission this evening for conducting talks with Crimea. It 
has been revealed that Simferopol's delegation at these talks 
will be headed by Sergey Tsekov, head of the Crimean Supreme 
Soviet. Yevgeniy Saburov, the head of government of the Republic 
of Crimea, expressed a hope in an interview with our radio 
station that the talks will be successful, the conflict 
resolved, and the situation in the Crimea will remain quiet. 
  [Begin Saburov recording] We continue to work in a calm 
manner. Crimea does not respond -- tries not to respond -- to 
provocations. Crimea is living its normal peaceful life. The 
Crimean Government is at the moment working on a report about 
the socioeconomic situation in the Republic, which is very poor. 
The Kiev leaders are disseminating false reports that the 
situation in Crimea is unstable and unquiet and because of this 
people are not coming here very much. I would like to tell you 
that the situation in Crimea is absolutely stable and quiet. No 
one is really interested in these bickerings between 
authorities. The weather here is marvelous and we look forward 
to seeing you all! [end recording] 

</TEXT>

