<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Meshkov Calls for Implementation 3-Party Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meshkov Calls for Implementation 3-Party Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105201294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1702 GMT 21 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105201294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Dzyublo] </F>
  [Text] Moscow 21 May TASS -- Crimean President Yuriy 
Meshkov called for guarantees of the implementation of the 
three-party agreement on the Crimea signed by Russia, Ukraine 
and the United States. 
  Speaking on Russian television on Saturday [21 May], Meshkov 
said that "we recognise our responsibility both to the people of 
Ukraine and the people of Russia" for possible consequences that 
the current developments may entail. He stressed that the 
Crimea's "willingness to work things out" must be "supported and 
guaranteed by all sides." 
  He described as "understandable" the situation when "the 
most 
acute problem of the Black Sea Fleet" based in the peninsula "is 
being solved without the participation of the Republic of 
Crimea." Meshkov emphasised that the problem "affects residents 
of the Republic of Crimea" and their interests. 
  He confirmed his intention "to solve all disputes on the 
basis of mutually beneficial and mutually acceptable terms." 
Meshkov said that at first the Crimea and Ukraine must sign an 
agreement in order to stabilise the situation and create 
conditions for signing an agreement between Russia and Ukraine. 
  He stressed that this must be done in exactly this order, 
not 
vice versa. The president warned that the opposite may put the 
Crimea outside the settlement process and have a negative impact 
on the talks. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

