<H3> <TI>   Odessa Military Denies Reports of Troops Movement in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Odessa Military Denies Reports of Troops Movement in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005151294 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1410 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005151294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Odessa, 20 May -- Colonel Vyacheslav Voronkov, press 
secretary of the Odessa military district commander, refuted 
reports by the "Ostankino" TV company about Ukrainian troops 
movements, which took place in Crimea. He said information 
about the movement of Ukrainian tanks in the vicinity of the 
village of Tylovoye, about the deployment of a field hospital in 
the village of Chernobayevka, and about the movement of the 
special purpose troops do not correspond to reality. The 32d 
Army Corps also remains in its deployment site. A routine 
inspection is being carried out in the Odessa military district 
units. A similar inspection will get under way in Crimea on 23 
May. 

