<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry on World Support for Ukraine Over Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry on World Support for Ukraine Over Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005180794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2005180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press center of our state's Foreign Affairs 
Ministry reported today the deep concern of the world community 
in connection with the Crimean events, directed at changing the 
legal status of the autonomous republic as a constituent part of 
Ukraine. Their disquietude is also evoked by tendencies, which 
lead to tension in interethnic relations on the peninsula and 
threaten peace and calm in the region. The report by the press 
center of Ukraine's Foreign Affairs Ministry notes that the 
European and world community, in the person of official factors 
and the mass media, is expressing its support for the principles 
of Ukraine's territorial integrity and the inviolability of its 
borders. They are also calling on political forces, which are 
destabilizing the situation in this region, to a balanced 
approach and the understanding of their responsibility to 
mankind. 

</TEXT>

