<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry Denounces Grachev for Rumors About Troops </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry Denounces Grachev for Rumors About Troops </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105142594 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1345 
GMT 21 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2105142594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev, 21 May -- The Ukrainian Defense Ministry has 
described as "nothing but rumors" the reports in the Russian 
media on the concentration of Ukrainian troops near Sevastopol 
and Simferopol. 
  "This blatant lie is being circulated with references to 
Russian Defense Minister Pavel Grachev, which is surprising, to 
say the least," said the Ukrainian Defense Ministry's press 
service today. "It remains to be guessed whether this is another 
political ploy of the Russian defense minister or merely his 
habitual trust in dubious sources of information." 
  The Ukrainian Defense Ministry's press service is authorized 
to declare that "the interference of the Russian Federation 
Defense Ministry in the affairs of the united Black Sea Fleet 
which, under the Yalta agreement, is subordinated directly to 
the presidents of Ukraine and Russia, stands in the way of a 
civilized solution to the fleet division issue and creates a 
dangerous tension in the situation in the Crimea." 

</TEXT>

