<H3> <TI>   Crimean Supreme Soviet Suspends Kravchuk Decrees in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Supreme Soviet Suspends Kravchuk Decrees in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2005200094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1740 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2005200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM-TASS correspondent Lev Ryabchikov] </F>
  [Text] Simferopol 20 May TASS -- At its evening meeting on 
Friday [20 May] the Crimean parliament decided to suspend on the 
territory of the peninsula the Ukrainian president's decrees "on 
departments of Justice of the Ministry of Justice of Ukraine" 
and "on the Main Department of the Security Service in the 
Crimea." Deputies adopted this decision on the basis of the 
restored constitution of the Republic of the Crimea of 6 May 
1992. 
  A similar resolution concerning the Ukrainian president's 
decree on the main interior department of the Crimea under the 
Interior Ministry of Ukraine was adopted by deputies of the 
Crimean parliament on 19 May this year. 

