<DOCNO> FBIS4-63492 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drsov099_f_94031" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-SOV-94-099 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  20 May 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNA-UNSO Nationalists Call for Martial Law in Crimea </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNA-UNSO Nationalists Call for Martial Law in Crimea </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2105113594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2300 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2105113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 20 May -- The Ukrainian National 
Assembly-Ukrainian National Self-Defense Organization [UNA-UNSO] 
people's deputies have submitted a draft resolution on settling 
the crisis situation in Crimea for consideration by the Supreme 
Council session. The UNA-UNSO resolution makes the following 
provision: 
  1. All Crimean administrative structures should be 
disbanded. 
  2. Emergency martial law should be introduced on the 
territory of Crimea. 
  3. All Crimean officials who are guilty of inflaming 
interethnic animosity, separatism and extremism should be 
arrested and held criminally responsible. 
  4. Additional Army and National Guard units should be 
brought into the territory of the peninsula to protect the 
civilian population from extremists. 
  5. Crimea's status as a republic should be annulled. 
  6. The performance of administrative functions in Crimea 
should be temporarily entrusted to the Ministry of Defense. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

