<F P=103> LD2105103094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The press service of the Ukrainian Defense Ministry 
made a statement on Friday [20 May] evening reporting an attempt 
by a group of armed people on 19 May to seize a command post of 
Ukraine's combined air defense troops in Sevastopol. 
  However, (Vladimir Lepikhev), chairman of Crimea's security 
service, denied those reports at today's morning session of the 
Crimean parliament. 
  Meanwhile, INTERFAX has learned that the uncontrolled 
deployment of special purpose troops and Ukrainian National 
Guardsmen on the peninsula is continuing. During the night of 
20-21 May, around 250 National Guardsmen arrived in Sevastopol 
and redeployed on the territory of the Ukrainian armed forces 
naval institute. The arrival of another 350 to 400 Guardsmen in 
Sevastopol is expected in the near future. 

</TEXT>

