<H3> <TI>   Crimean Interior Ministry Controlling Government Buildings </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimean Interior Ministry Controlling Government Buildings </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2205085494 Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 0800 GMT 
22 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2205085494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Rossii Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Valeriy Gorbatov, the Ukrainian representative in 
Crimea, has told INTERFAX-Ukraine that the Crimean Republic's 
Interior Ministry on Saturday [21 May] took control of the main 
government buildings in the Crimea. 
  According to Gorbatov, the Crimean Interior Ministry units 
have been put on alert and have been given a basic supply of 
ammunition after a report that units of the National Guard in 
Simferopol were allegedly put on condition one combat readiness. 
  Valeriy Gorbatov said in this connection that in fact there 
has been no ground for the Interior Ministry's actions. In his 
words, units of the National Guard are in barracks and no 
measures to bring them to condition one combat readiness have 
been taken. 

